title: natural candy recipe(diabetic)
directions: Mix together peanut butter, carob, bananas and vanilla.
Shape into balls (one teaspoon each) and roll in cinnamon.
Press walnut half into each candy.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 64 pieces.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Add
potatoes,
corn,
onion and celery to three quarts broth. May
use
1/2 water and 1/2 broth.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add
chicken.
Bring to a boil and serve.
If using canned corn, add it when you add chicken.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornmeal and sugar.
Mix together eggs, margarine, Karo syrup and vanilla.
(Blender is not needed.)
Add to dry mixture.
Stir until mixed well.

title: spring temptation pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a medium bowl until completely dissolved.
Stir in sherbet.
Mix until melted. Refrigerate until gelatin is slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping, marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into crust; freeze until firm.

title: egg flip(aka preacher's snack at midnight)
directions: In a blender, mix milk, egg, vanilla and enough sugar to taste.
Blend at high speed to beat egg.
Add ice milk and blend to desired milk shake consistency.
Add bananas or peaches.

title: cheddar ham chowder
directions: In large saucepan, bring water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Remove from heat; do not drain.
In another saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk all at once; cook until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir into vegetables.
Return saucepan to heat.
Add corn and ham; heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans following package directions; drain.
Combine beans, soup and almonds in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle stuffing mix evenly on top.
Pour margarine on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: vienna apple cake
directions: Beat
together	egg
yolk, water, salt and lemon juice. Cream the
butter.
Blend
into
first
mixture.	Add
flour. Divide dough
in
half.
Roll
one piece out thin and fit into greased 12 x	6-inch	pan. Peel and core apples and chop fine with raisins and
almonds.
Spread mixture over dough in pan. Top with remaining dough, rolled out thin.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fried okra
directions: Thaw okra (if frozen) in bowl.
Combine flour, meal and pepper.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Dip okra in water (if using fresh okra).
Roll in mixture to coat.
Place on baking sheet; bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with toothpick with salt and catsup.

title: pound cake-blueberry
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and all eggs at one time. Add margarine (melted). Mix well. Add cake mix. Fold drained blueberries into batter. (Do not use mixer on blueberries; do not use juice.) Pour into well-greased (margarine), floured cake pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done (test with toothpick). Enjoy.

title: beef pinwheels
directions: Combine ingredients and set aside.
Prepare Baking Powder Biscuit Dough (see recipe in bread section).
Roll dough into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Spread meat mixture evenly over biscuit dough.
Starting with long side of dough, roll up and pinch edge to seal.
(Do not pinch ends of roll.)
Place on baking sheet, sealed edge down.
Bring ends of roll together to form a ring.
Brush ring lightly with melted butter.
With sharp knife, make cuts at 1-inch intervals around ring to within 1/4-inch of center.
Slightly pull and twist each section so that sides rest almost flat on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with brown gravy.

title: play dough
directions: Mix and cook over low heat until mixture starts to scrape from sides of pan and is thick.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring. Add cinnamon and peppermint oil for aroma, if desired.
Knead on waxed paper for a few minutes.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Add salt and pepper to milk-egg mixture.
Break up cauliflower.
Dip flowerets into egg mixture, then into flour and cheese mixture.
Brown in deep fat for 3 minutes.
Drain.

title: easy pumpkin swirl
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Line top and sides with waxed paper.
Grease waxed paper.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine together at room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls, then flatten.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: In a small bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat shrimp, cream cheese, cocktail sauce, celery and horseradish until well blended.
Cover; chill until serving.
Garnish with lemon slice and parsley sprig, if desired.
Serve as a dip with pretzel chips or crackers.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin; add berries, stirring well.
Stir in pineapple, bananas and lemon juice.
Divide mixture in 1/2 and add 1/2 in a 2-quart dish.
Put in refrigerator until thick.
Spread sour cream over jello mixture, then carefully spread the other half of jelly mixture, which was standing on counter, on top of the sour cream mixture.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: spaghetti cheese bake
directions: Boil spaghetti and drain.
Pour spaghetti into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle Romano cheese over all.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour evenly over spaghetti.
Pour whole jar Ragu over top.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Cut and serve.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream first four ingredients together.
Sift together next 6 ingredients.
Mix together and add cream mixture, then add zucchini.
Put in 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetarian lentil-barley soup
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, cook onion, celery and garlic in hot margarine until tender.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, lentils, barley, bouillon cubes, rosemary, oregano and pepper.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer for 15 minutes more or just until carrots are tender. Ladle into soup bowls and top with cheese.
Serves 5.

title: noodle pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Fold egg whites gently into mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Add dots of butter to top.
Bake in a glass pan at 350° for 45 minutes or in a metal pan at 375° for 45 minutes. Enjoy.
You will lick the pan clean!

title: chocolate peanut butter snacks
directions: Spread about 1 teaspoon of peanut butter on
half of crackers; top with remaining crackers.
Melt the chocolate flavored candy coating in top of double boiler.
Dip sandwich crackers in coating, allowing excess to drain off.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook rice.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add all other ingredients together in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna-cheese-macaroni loaf
directions: Heat evaporated milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan over low heat until just below boiling point. Add cheese; stir until thickened and smooth.
Beat eggs slightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add cheese sauce.
Combine thoroughly.
Place in well buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes before turning out on a warm platter.
Serve with additional cheese sauce, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pasta con broccoli(favorite from pasta house)
directions: Cook and drain macaroni and steam broccoli.
Melt margarine. Add half and half, tomato sauce and cheese.
Add macaroni; simmer until cheese is melted.
Add steamed broccoli and fresh mushrooms. Serve when mushrooms are heated through.

title: beef and kraut casserole
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly. Alternate mixture in casserole with sauerkraut.
Add water until it comes to top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in large container.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add peanut butter; mix well. Roll into walnut size balls; lay out on wax paper.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together over hot water.
Dip each ball in chocolate mixture.
(I use a fork to lift the balls in and out of the chocolate.)
The balls will cool quickly and be pretty and glossy.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and half of tomato sauce into a loaf.
For sauce, mix remaining half of tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, sugar and mustard.
In a saucepan bring to a boil.
Pour half of the sauce over meat loaf and bake 40 minutes.
Then pour remaining sauce over and bake 50 minutes for a total of 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Bake covered for first hour.

title: chicken pan deluxe
directions: Mix together the first 2 ingredients and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Heat all liquids.
Mix everything together.
Pour over stuffing.
Put the reserved stuffing on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: grandma yerak's nut torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease two 9-inch layer cake pans. Separate all eggs; beat egg whites and 1/2 of sugar until stiff in a large bowl; set aside.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks and remaining sugar until thick.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt into egg yolk mixture and beat.
Stir in maple syrup.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites with walnuts and chocolate.
Pour into pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, split each layer in two, making 4 layers.
Prepare whipped cream filling; beat whipping cream and sugar together until stiff and peaky. Spread between layers and over top of cake.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown onion with beef and drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans.
Heat until bubbly. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Separate biscuits and cut each in half.
Place cut side down around dish.
Bake about 20 minutes just until biscuits brown.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake a few minutes until melted.

title: angel hair spaghetti with tuna sauce
directions: In saucepan, put olive oil, tuna and parsley.
Add salt and pepper; cook for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes more, but don't burn garlic.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water for 10 minutes while you're making the sauce.
Drain spaghetti, place in large bowl and mix in tuna sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and serve.
If desired, add more cheese.

title: peggy's appetizer
directions: Blend together real well.
Roll up in ham slices, cut slices in 3 pieces after rolling.
Secure with toothpick.
Top with olives and/or cubes of cheese.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Sprinkle in some bacon bits.
Toss all together.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Split cake into 3 layers.
Have cheese and Cool Whip at room temperature.
Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Spread between layers.
Pour cherries on the top and sides and let it run down in the center hole of the cake.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Roll out rolls.
Press together with fingers.
Pour on beaten egg and pour off excess egg.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Remove and cool.
Spread 1/2 to 3/4 bottle of dressing.
Sprinkle on cauliflower and broccoli.
Top with shredded cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Mash enough strawberries to fill one cup.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water and mashed strawberries gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute and then cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Steam Veg-All for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix with 1/4 lb. Velveeta cheese (use more cheese if you like).
Put into casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Mix with 1 stick melted butter. Sprinkle cracker and butter mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss veggies with cheese and bacon.

title: nutty chocolate cups
directions: In small bowl, combine chocolate wafer crumbs and butter; mix well.
Spoon 1 tablespoon crumb mixture into each of 12 foil lined muffin cups; press firmly.
Set aside remaining cookie crumbs.
In medium saucepan over low heat, combine half and half, 1 2/3 cups marshmallows and milk chocolate chips.
Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; cool completely. Fold in whipped cream, remaining 1/3 cup marshmallows and cashews. Pour 1/3 cup into each prepared muffin cup.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Freeze until firm (about 1 hour).

title: chocolate nut wafers
directions: In a medium bowl combine chopped nuts, flour, cloves and salt.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cover soup bones with cold water; bring to boil.
Skim off top foam.
Keep barely boiling for 2 to 3 hours.
Add rest of ingredients (tomatoes, optional).
Cook until noodles are done. Cool soup, remove bones and dice meat.
Skim fat off soup.
Freeze in smaller containers for eating later.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° until done.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 13-inch pan.
May be frozen for later, if wished.

title: berry-banana smoothies
directions: In a blender, combine the orange juice, sherbet, sliced banana and the strawberries. Cover and process until smooth. Pour into chilled glasses and enjoy!

title: huckleberry glaze or blueberry
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Put into saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup of cold water and stir over medium-high heat.
(Stir as burner warms up to get cornstarch to dissolve.) If it thickens too fast, remove temporarily from heat.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add buttermilk, eggs and bananas. Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°. Test with a toothpick until done.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix 1/2 cup pork or chicken broth with flour to make stiff dough.
Roll out real thin.
Cut into strips.
Have about 1 pint of broth plus 1 quart water all boiling together. Drop strips of dough into boiling pot. Do not stir.
Drop all strips into pot. Turn down low and cook for about 15 minutes.
Add lots of black pepper.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Fill pie shell with sliced apples.
Heat apple juice to boiling.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and stir into hot juice. Cook until thickened.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Dot with butter.
Pour juice over all and cover with upper crust.
Prick crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rosemary carrots
directions: Place carrots in a 2-quart casserole dish.
In small bowl, combine bouillon, water, brown sugar and seasonings.
Pour over carrots; toss to coat and cover.
Microwave on High power 5 to 8 minutes, or until carrots are tender, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add sugar, cinnamon and salt to beaten eggs and mix well.
Add oil.
Combine baking soda, baking powder and flour and add to mixture.
Fold in zucchini, nuts and vanilla.
Divide batter into 2 (9-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Will freeze indefinitely.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved. Stir in lukewarm water.
Add beaten egg and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in additional 3 cups flour.
Place dough in greased bowl; brush top with soft shortening.
Cover tightly with foil. Store in refrigerator until double in bulk or needed, up to 1 week.
When ready to use, shape and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Brush with butter while hot.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together Thousand Island dressing and sugar.
Brown meat and drain; add taco seasoning.
Set aside and cool.
Chop all vegetables and mix with Doritos, kidney beans and Cheddar cheese. Add dressing and sugar mixture to this.
Once cooled, add meat. Chill and serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Coat chicken in Cavender's and saute in skillet sprayed with Pam over medium heat until done (approx. 15 minutes or until juices run clear).
Remove from heat.
While chicken is cooking, heat spaghetti sauce in a separate pan.
Cook pasta according to package directions and drain.
Then toss with margarine to keep from drying out.
Place on serving portion of pasta on each plate. Place a chicken breast on top of pasta.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of sauce over each and immediately sprinkle with grated cheeses. Serve immediately.

title: chicken and mushroom dijon
directions: In skillet, use 1 tablespoon oleo to cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove chicken and add other 1 tablespoon of oleo to cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender, stirring often.
Add soup, milk and mustard.
Heat to boiling and then add chicken again.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Goes good with noodles.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add enough of the water to make paste.
Beat in egg yolks well.

title: meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan.
Drain all fat off.
Brown sausage until cooked.

Slice them up and mix with the ground beef. Pour in tomtato sauce, tomato paste, crushed tomato, oregano, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper and garlic powder and simmer for approximately 1 hour or until as thick as you would like.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix green beans, corn, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup together and put in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli fine (stem and all).
Add onions, raisins, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss lightly together.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.
Let set 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: english hot pot
directions: Pour cup of water in a baking pan.
Place layer of onion on bottom of pan, then potatoes, then carrots.
Repeat.
Place pork chops on top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: lemon rice pilaf
directions: Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and saute until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add rice and saute for 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt. Makes 6 servings.

title: maple mousse magnifique
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Combine Marshmallow Creme and sour cream, mixing with electric mixer or wire whisk until well balanced.
Add ice cream, nuts and flavoring; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour over crust.
Freeze.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and chocolate curls, if desired.
Serve immediately from freezer.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Drain beets; set aside.
Add enough water to beet juice to measure 1 cup.
Combine beet juice, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan; bring to a slow boil.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved. Pour syrup over beets in a glass crock or jar.
Add 5 or 6 whole cloves and onion slices for extra flavor.
Add eggs to beets and syrup.
Store in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal raisin apple muffins
directions: Beat egg, stir in remaining ingredients just to moisten.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups, 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve cool or hot with butter.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Sift first 7 ingredients together 3 times.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and sugar for 6 minutes.
Fold in dry ingredients by hand.

title: dimple cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients and drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Put a dimple in each cookie with your finger or thumb and fill with your favorite jam.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fajitas
directions: Cut steak or chicken into strips.
Mix all ingredients except for tortillas, lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and picante sauce. Marinate steak/chicken for 8 hours.
(Can marinate up to 24 hours.)
Turn steak/chicken after 4 hours and continue to marinate.
Stir-fry or grill steak/chicken.
Place on tortilla. Serve with lettuce, tomato, picante sauce and sour cream.

title: beef-macaroni skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion in Dutch oven.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, until macaroni is done (about 12 to 15 minutes).

title: pan stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Add mixed vegetables and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: denver pork chops
directions: Season pork chops.
Coat both sides with sour cream and the corn flake crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Really crisp and good.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit; save juice.
Add water if necessary to make 6 cups.
Add juice to pudding and tapioca.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Let cool.
Add chilled fruit.
Keeps 1 week in refrigerator.
Add 3 sliced bananas before serving.

title: bran muffins(refrigerated)
directions: *Or use 5 cups plain flour with 5 teaspoons soda and 1 tablespoon salt, sifted together.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs; add dry ingredients.
After cake batter is mixed well, mix in apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan 35 - 45 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put 1 cup water in boiler.
Heat to boiling.
Add Jell-O, stir in 1/2 cup marshmallows.
Let cool, then add pineapple and juice, applesauce and 1 cup water with gelatin.
Whip Dream Whip and fold into mixture.
Chill.

title: corn, rice and bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice, beans, corn, scallions and jalapeno peppers.
Toss to mix.
In a small bowl, combine the oil, lime juice, vinegar, brown sugar, salt, cumin and chili powder. Whisk to blend well and dissolve the sugar.
Pour the dressing over the salad.
Toss to coat.
Let stand at room temperature, tossing occasionally, for up to 4 hours before serving or cover and refrigerate for up to 3 days.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly chocolate sauce
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Keeps in refrigerator. Great on ice cream for sundaes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Beat together all ingredients except cucumbers.
Fold cucumbers into mixture.
Some chopped onion can be added.
Serve in sauce dishes and garnish with paprika.

title: apple crisp
directions: Layer apples in greased pie plate.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg together.
Put on top of apples.
Sprinkle melted butter on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in vanilla, coconut, oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes or until light brown.
I usually double this recipe.

title: chocolate sweet cake
directions: Mix in saucepan and bring to a boil the margarine, Crisco, cocoa, water and vanilla.
Mix in another bowl the sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Remove mixture from stove and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well and add eggs and buttermilk. Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with vegetables or Fritos chips.

title: fresh fruit shell salad
directions: Prepare shells as package directs.
Drain.
In small bowl, blend yogurt and orange juice concentrate.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add yogurt mixture.
Toss to coat. Cover and chill. Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine with syrup, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and milk in heavy pan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or 234°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: microwave clam chowder
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, cook bacon and onions for 5 minutes on High.
Add potatoes, liquid from clams and water.
Cook 15 to 18 minutes.
Stir every 4 minutes.
Add clams, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with cream cheese, soup and 1 can of onion rings.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix until fluffy. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in apples, raisins and nuts.
Put into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave cake in for another 1/2 hour. Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: black bean and smoked chicken soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place a heavy stockpot over medium heat for about 1 minute, then spray it twice with the vegetable oil. Add the broccoli stems, carrot, celery, and onion.
Cover, reduce the heat to low, and cook for 5 minutes, stirring once or twice. Stir in the thyme, basil, and wine.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 15 minutes, until the wine has been reduced by half.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Mix all together. Drop in hot oil by tsp. using only half teaspoon they get big roll in cinnamon sugar or powdered sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and beat until light yellow.
Add oil, zucchini and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to zucchini mixture and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: straw and hay
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water.
Drain and toss with 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Cover and set aside.
Melt remaining butter in large saucepan.
Saute garlic until golden.
Spoon out garlic and discard.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add persimmons, sugar, melted butter and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and spices.
Start mixing and adding milk gradually.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: turkey crescents
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Separate dough into four rectangles. Put 1/2 cup mixture into center of rectangle.
Bring four corners up and twist.
Brush top with rest of butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with gravy.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: mom's cheese soup
directions: Add potatoes, carrots, onions and bouillon cubes to water. Cook until carrots are tender. Add cauliflower and broccoli; cook until tender. Add cans of cream of chicken soup and stir well. Add Velveeta cheese. Stir in and let melt.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in large saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Cream sugar, shortening and oleo.
Add egg yolks one at a time; beaten well after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour and cream mixture.
Stir in coconut and pecans; stiffly beat egg white and fold in.
Pour into 3 x 9-inch layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: molded avocado salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add mayonnaise and beat until frothy.
Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Add pineapple juice, lemon juice and cold water to gelatin mixture and blend well. Add crushed pineapple and avocados.
Pour into 8-inch square Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and place each square on lettuce leaf to serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: plaza iii steak soup
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and gradually add 2 cups water (roux).
Stir until smooth.
Add all other ingredients, except steak.

title: that bean dip stuff
directions: Layer in pan or bowl, starting with the bean dip, being sure that the entire bottom is covered with dip.
Serve with chips.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Combine vanilla pudding and 3 cups milk. Mix well and cook in microwave, stirring often, until thickens. Cool completely. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Place 8 graham crackers in bottom of 9x13 inch dish. Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers. Top with 8 more crackers and remaining pudding mixture. Top with the remaining 8 crackers. Mix the chocolate pudding with remaining 1 1/2 cups milk. (I add a little extra milk, it tends to get a little too thick.) Cook in microwave until it begins to thicken. Cool slightly. Pour over top layer of crackers while warm enough to spread easily. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight to chill and soften crackers. 18 servings. Sliced strawberries may be served on top as a garnish.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix with a fork.
Press crumbs into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Melt margarine.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until a smooth, soft dough forms.
Cover tight; refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 3 days.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Make balls out of dough and roll in sugar mixture. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: baked french bread
directions: Butter large baking dish. In medium bowl, beat eggs, milk, cream, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cut bread into 1-inch slices. Place sliced bread in baking dish, single layer with sides touching. Pour entire mixture over bread.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Add oleo and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in powdered sugar and beat again until smooth.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Measure dry ingredients and mix thoroughly (except celery seed).
Add grated onion and small amount of vinegar.
Add oil and remaining vinegar gradually, beating after each addition.
Add the celery seed which has been soaked in the water.
Makes about 1 pint.
Great on cole slaw and chicken. Keep in refrigerator. Shake well before using.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix 3 ingredients together.
Mixture will resemble sticky paste.
Place in lightly greased bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Mix chicken and cheese together. Place heaping tablespoon of chicken and cheese mixture on crescent roll.
Roll from big to small end.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish, sprayed with Pam.

title: cowboy biscuits
directions: Saute ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off grease.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Place biscuits in greased muffin cup, pressing to cover bottom and sides of cups.
Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana-pineapple cake
directions: You will need 1 large and 1 medium mixing bowl, 1 large tube or Bundt pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish add raw rice, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Mix well with about 1/2 cup of milk.
Pour the rest of the milk in to about 1/2 inch from top of dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour, at 350°. Thickens as it cools.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Into whipped egg whites fold in sugar, pecans and chocolate chips.
Spoon by hand onto aluminum foil which is several sheets thick.
Put cookies into oven and then turn oven off.
Wait 5 hours.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears; reserve syrup.
Combine with candy, heat until dissolve.
Add pears.
Bring to a boil. Chill pears in syrup overnight.
Blend cheese with lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drain pears.
Place filling in center of pears. Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Cream all together, except bacon bites. Roll into balls, then roll in the bacon bites.
Refrigerate for 1 to 3 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Tie spices in a bag.
Dissolve lime in water.
Put in cucumbers which have been sliced.
Let soak for 24 hours.
Remove and wash well in 3 or 4 changes of water.
Make a solution of the sugar, salt, vinegar and spices.
Pour over pickles and let soak 3 hours, then boil 30 minutes to seal.

title: quick chess pie
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar; let cool. Add 3 eggs, one at a time and then add vinegar.
Pour into pie shell, bake 30 minutes at 350° or until browned on top.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine in bowl: green beans, yellow wax beans, red kidney beans, onion, green bell pepper and pimento, mix well. In sauce pan combine sugar, salt, pepper, oil, and vinegar. Heat on stove until it comes to a boil. Pour over mixture of vegetables. Cool and put in refrigerator. Stir gently 3 or 4 times before serving.

title: lemon-herb chicken
directions: Prepare Lemon-Herb Marinade.
Place chicken in rectangular microwavable dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inches.
Pour marinade over chicken; turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, turning chicken occasionally.

title: louise wetmore's frosting
directions: Beat together all ingredients except confectioners sugar.
Add confectioners sugar as needed, adding until the desired consistency has been reached.

title: hopping john
directions: Rinse dry peas.
In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine peas and 6 cups water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover.
Let stand 1 hour (or soak peas overnight in a covered pan).
Drain peas and rinse.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 hour, then bring to a boil. Boil 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and add the Jell-O. Stir well. Add the pie filling. Stir well. Return to heat and stir thoroughly, but don't boil. Store in container. Enjoy.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the eggs and sugar.
Add oil.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add apples and nuts to coat.
Mix all ingredients.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into greased and floured tube (Bundt) pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Beat Eagle Brand milk with the juice of 2 lemons; add drained fruit cocktail, 1 cup of nuts, coconut and Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Decorate top with mandarin orange slices and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: oat-bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin cups with Pam.
Combine dry ingredients; add milk, egg and oil.
Mix until dry ingredients are moist.
Add raisins.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake 17 minutes.

title: the great puffy pancake
directions: Heat
oven
to
Mix
the
flour,
milk, eggs and nutmeg slightly with beater or whip.
Melt the margarine in a large frypan.
Pour
the batter into the melted margarine and bake
15 to 20 minutes until puffed and brown.
Squeeze on the lemon juice and lightly dust with confectioners sugar.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted. Add marshmallow cream; stir until melted.
Pour in greased pan. Cool.
Make 3 pounds.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, soda and baking powder in a mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients into Pyrex pan (5 1/2 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch) and spread level in pan.
Make 3 little wells and add vinegar, vanilla and vegetable oil.
Gradually pour over this 1 cup cold water.
Mix thoroughly.
Add 1/3 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake in same dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with margarine.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread on top of cookies. Refreeze.
Bring to a boil the sugar, evaporated milk, vanilla, chocolate and margarine.
Boil for 1 minute; cool.
Pour over ice cream and freeze.
Mix Cool Whip with nuts and spread over chocolate.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in large roaster.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 3 hours.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: lemon buttah
directions: Melt buttah; add lemun juise, aigs and sugah.
Mix 'n stir in the grated lemun rind.
Cook in a double boiler til done.

title: vegetable barley soup
directions: If using long-cooking barley, rinse barley in colander and remove any foreign objects.
In small soup pot, combine barley with meat stock or broth.
Cook over medium heat about 1 hour. Add carrots, celery, onion, tomatoes, thyme and bay leaf. Continue cooking for 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms and zucchini and if using quick cooking barley, add it now.
Cook over low heat another 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings (1 cup each).

title: green beans with almonds
directions: Place
green beans in kettle of salted water with sugar added. Cook,
covered,
until
barely
tender
(from 10 to 25 minutes). Drain but keep hot for serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Place noodles and spinach in alternate layers, in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour white sauce over spinach.
Bake in moderate 350° oven until browned. Serves 6.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Totally submerge unopened can in large pot of boiling water. Keep water at slow boil for 3 hours, adding more boiling water occasionally to keep can submerged.
Open cooled can and Voila!

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soften bread crumbs in 1 cup milk.
Add beef, onion, eggs and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls.
Heat butter in a large skillet; add meatballs and stir 1/3 cup flour (increase?) into drippings.
Dissolve beef cubes in hot water and gradually add to flour mixture.
Add milk and cream.
Cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Add meatballs and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes large pan for hors d'oeuvres or serve over noodles.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and butter.
Cook on medium heat to a firm ball stage. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and beat until it loses its glossy appearance. Put on greased plates and cool. Cut into squares.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: southern chicken pie
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex or pan with butter.
Add chicken pieces and slice 1/2 stick butter over chicken.
Mix soup and broth together and pour over chicken.
Mix milk and Bisquick until smooth and pour over chicken with broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered, until brown.
Can add vegetables if desired.

title: mock cinnamon rolls
directions: Make Uris' Easy Biscuit recipe.
Roll out to a 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Spread with margarine.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Add chopped nuts.
Roll up and pinch ends closed.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.
Bake at 375° on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and Jell-O.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add berries and beat 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cream oleo and add powdered sugar and berries alternately.
Frost cake.

title: new england anadama bread
directions: Place first 2 ingredients in a bowl, stir to combine and let stand 1 hour.
Then add molasses or cane syrup, salt and butter or Crisco.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine the yeast and warm water (105° to 115°) until dissolved.
Let stand until "foamy" (about 5 minutes).
Add to corn meal and molasses mixture and work in about 4 1/2 cups flour.
Knead thoroughly until smooth and elastic on a floured surface.
Shape into loaves (makes 2) and place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double and bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until golden brown and loaf sounds hollow when thwacked with fingers.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and lemonade.
Blend with mixer until well blended and stiff.
Add Cool Whip; fold in with spoon.
Mix together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Butter sides and bottoms of a miniature muffin pan (will need 4).
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs; shake to cover.
Mix well the cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks.
Beat the egg whites very stiff and fold into mixture.
Fill pans almost to the top. Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove promptly.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add Crisco; mix until size of peas.
Add water.
Knead until smooth.
Divide dough.
Will make 3 pie crusts. Can be frozen.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Combine
all ingredients in crock-pot on low.
Mix well until melted.
Serve as an appetizer with nachos, tacos, baked potatoes or potato skins.

title: green rice with spinach
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add onion, garlic, bell pepper and jalapeno; saute for 5 to 7 minutes, until onions are tender.
Add water, rice, parsley, cumin, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Simmer over medium heat for about 15 minutes (if using brown rice, 45 minutes).
Stir in spinach and cilantro; cook over low heat for about 5 minutes more, until rice is tender. Serves 4.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken in water with bouillon cube until well done. Save the chicken broth.
Chop up the chicken.
Mix 2 cups of the chicken broth with cream of chicken soup and heat.
Combine the mixture with the canned LeSueur peas.
Spread chopped chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour vegetable and soup mixture over chicken.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers for 1 hour in ice cubes by packing layer of sliced cucumbers, layer of ice cubes.
Combine sliced onions, vinegar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and cloves and bring to a boil. Pour in drained cucumbers and simmer until color changes and cucumbers are tender, about 1 hour.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: instant strawberry ice cream
directions: Just before serving, remove berries from freezer.
Place cream, eggs and sugar in blender.
Whirl 2 seconds with motor on high.
Drop in frozen berries, one at a time, by removing center part of blender lid.
Whirl until smooth, stopping when necessary to stir thick mixture with rubber scraper.
Spoon in dishes and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Fill cupcake liners 2/3 full with batter.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add chips.
Put 1 teaspoon of this filling in center of cupcakes.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cupcakes.

title: chocolate chip-cream cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and vegetable oil until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping; pat remaining crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls out on 12-inch pizza pan. Layer sausage, potatoes and cheese on dough.
Beat together the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits until fine.
Stir biscuits, sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla, milk and butter.
For chocolate, add 3 tablespoons cocoa.
For vanilla, add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: betty cliff's salad
directions: Layer ingredients.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over peas or peas over Parmesan cheese.
Put grated Cheddar cheese on top.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Make sandwiches with ham and cheese.
Put rolls back into trays.
Melt butter, poppy seed, onion and mustard in microwave. Spoon over top of each tray of rolls.
Cover with foil and bake until heated and cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until white and fluffy.
Sift flour and cornstarch and add to creamed mixture.
Knead until smooth.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven; cover with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and celery.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken and cool.
Cool broth; remove fat. Skin and bone chicken; dice meat.

title: mexican trainwreck
directions: Brown together meat and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add spices; stir in liquids.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour or in crock-pot until ready to serve.
Let each person put his own trainwreck together in somewhat the following order:
A layer of corn chips, rice, meat sauce, cheese, etc. with the following condiments:

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Roll bread into rectangular size.
On each loaf, divide sausage, cheese, parsley and onion.
Spread. Dribble egg over each loaf. Roll bread into jelly roll. Form and pinch edges and seal with water. Baste egg over rolls and bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: mud pie(chocolate icebox pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix flour, oleo, and ground pecans to make crust. Spread in 11 X 13 casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes. Let cool.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and 2/3 cup water.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat, add fruit and cool.
Beat cream cheese and Eagle Brand until smooth.
Combine with gelatin and pecans.
Mix well, pour into mold or 9-inch square Pyrex dish.
Serves 16 people. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: bisquick buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.
Pour in greased pie plate and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. This pie makes it own crust.

title: mini-ha-ha cake
directions: Mix together and bake in layer pans or sheet cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into bite-sized pieces; place in Dutch oven or any ovenproof pan.
Salt beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake covered at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: fruit cocktail mystery pudding
directions: Drain fruit
cocktail,	reserving
1/4	cup syrup.
Mix together flour, white
sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar,
reserved syrup and egg; blend well.
Stir in drained fruit cocktail and nuts; mix well.

title: pastry for two-crust pies(yields 56 portions - 7 pies)
directions: Mix flour and shortening on low speed for 1 minute, using pastry knife or flat beater.
Scrape sides of bowl and continue mixing until shortening is evenly distributed, 1 to 2 minutes. Dissolve salt in smaller amount of water (use reserved amount if water is needed).
Add to flour mixture.
Mix on low speed only until dough is formed, about 40 seconds.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix.
Cover with bread crumbs and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked chicken in casserole.
Add soups on top.
Mix stuffing with chicken broth and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until top is brown and bubbles.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with dry soup. Add Tater Tots.
Pour canned soup and milk (mixed together) over top.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° covered for 1 hour or until slightly brown.
Quick and easy!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients except sour cream.
Divide in half.
Put half in another container and half in refrigerator to congeal.
Put 1 pint sour cream on top of hard jello.
Put other half in refrigerator and partially set.
Then pour or spoon on top of sour cream.
Chill. Serves 12.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and pour into bowl.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish. Add onion and cook on High 1 1/2 minutes. Add soup and cheese. Cook 30 seconds.
Stir. When cheese is melted, add remaining ingredients and cook on High 12 to 15 minutes.

title: vampire punch
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Cool in a large bowl.
Combine pineapple and strawberries and juice.
Chill.
Add cooled sugar syrup to fruit mixture and refrigerate.
Just before serving, add club soda to juice.
Makes eight 2-cup servings.

title: saucepan spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir water, tomato sauce, onion, oregano, basil, salt, garlic powder and pepper into the pan with the meat.
Cook mixture until bubbly.
Break spaghetti in half and add to the saucepan.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 30 minutes. Serve with grated cheese.
Enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and add chopped chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable stuffed peppers(serves 4)
directions: Cut off tops of bell peppers. Remove seeds; rinse and set to dry. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onions, garlic, zucchini, tomatoes and salt. Saute until zucchini begins to get tender; do not overcook. In a medium bowl, combine rice and cheese. Add to tomato mixture and toss gently to mix well. Spoon mixture into peppers and arrange in an 8-inch casserole dish. Pour tomato juice over and around peppers. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: rice for all dishes
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender, for at least 4 minutes.
Add dry rice and cook for approximately 2 minutes more or until rice is coated well with margarine.
Add the curry powder and water.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes or until all the water is absorbed.

title: black-eyed peas and ham hocks
directions: Bring all ingredients, except okra, to a boil.
Then simmer until meat is tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Add okra 30 minutes before cooking is completed.
Serve over hot rice.

title: creole peas
directions: Cook peas and drain.
In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender, but not brown.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add tomatoes to cooked onion.
Stir in peas, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Blend tomato liquid into cornstarch. Stir into pea mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.

title: sausage-potato casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of potatoes in greased casserole dish.
Add 1/2 of flour, pepper and salt over potatoes, then add 1/2 sausage and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Combine and toss potatoes, celery, green pepper, parsley and onion.
Add milk, salt and Tabasco sauce and mix well.
Put mixture in skillet and press in firmly.
Cover and cook on LOW heat until done and crust has formed on bottom and sides of potatoes (about 30 minutes).
Invert on plate and cut into wedges to serve.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook over medium-low heat about six minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
To serve, slice biscuits and spoon gravy over the halves.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Take pan and layer chips, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine water and 1/2 cup butter; bring to a rolling boil. Add flour.
Stir into a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly after each.
Form into a ring on an ungreased cooking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely away from draft.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Break 1 head of lettuce in chunks in salad bowl.
Top with 6 1/2 ounce can crab meat or shrimp, 2 sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Pour dressing over salad.

title: bleu cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add Bleu cheese to taste.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Good for chip dip also or with wings and celery.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Pare and cube eggplant.
Cook for 5 minutes in boiling water. Drain and mash.
Stir in Ritz crackers, cheese, beaten eggs, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties and fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes, on each side.
Serves 4.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 2 tablespoons juice. Set beets and juice aside. In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar, orange juice and beet juice. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Add beets and orange peel.
Heat through.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: royal pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in cold water and pear juice, lemon juice and cranberry sauce.
(Break up cranberry sauce a little before adding to mixture.)
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in chopped pears and pecans.
Spoon into a 7-cup mold or a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: white pfeffernusse
directions: Mix all ingredients together into a cookie dough.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Make into small balls and bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Add all other ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Let rest in bowl 5 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out and pat into two 12-inch oiled pizza pans.
Add pizza toppings and bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until done.

title: oyster loaf
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, onion and garlic.
Roll out flat on wax paper.
Drain juice from oysters; chop up very fine and spread oysters over mixture.
Roll up; cut off the ends so one can see the spiral of oysters.
Keep refrigerated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ground beef, oats, eggs, onion, seasonings and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Mold into loaf in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine remaining tomato sauce. Pour over loaf and bake 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into walnut size balls; flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix it.
Then you take two eggs, crack the eggs and put them in there and spoon them around.
Put milk in and then you stir it. Put 32 Oreos.
Crack them into two pieces and put them in the chocolate cake.
Put some sugar, powder and icing inside the bowl. Put the cake into the oven and bake it.
Bake it 5 minutes at 5°. Then you put 6 candles on and that's all of it.

title: funny paper cake
directions: Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Mix ingredients.
Divide mixture into four parts.
Pour one part of the mixture into the tube pan.
In second part put 5 drops of green food coloring.
Mix and pour around center of pan.
With third part add 3 drops of red food coloring and 1 tablespoon of almond extract.
Mix and then pour into tube pan.
In fourth part mix in 1 square of melted chocolate.
Pour into tube pan and swirl the colors.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: baked soft-shell crabs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Rinse crabs under cold water and drain. Place them in a shallow baking pan.
Melt butter and add lemon juice and parsley.

title: spicy hot tea mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Store in airtight container. Use 1 to 2 tablespoons per cup of hot water (or as much as desired).

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Divide pastry into 2 parts and roll thin to fit an 8 or 9-inch plate; set aside.
Mix apples, apple juice concentrate, thickener and spice; stir until apples are well coated.
Add lemon juice, if desired, to keep apples lighter in color.
Taste 1 piece of apple to check the spice.

title: herb butter
directions: Beat all together at high speed in a small mixing bowl until fluffy.
Keep in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: cider baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place ham in a large roasting pan. Bake for 30 minutes or until outside is crisp.
Remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: country borsch
directions: In large covered saucepan, simmer meat in broth and water for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir in salt, onion, beets, potato, carrot and celery; cover and simmer 15 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cabbage; cook until just tender. Combine flour and lemon juice; slowly add to soup.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except sour cream and croutons.
Cook, stirring occasionally until mixture thickens.
Serve hot, garnished with sour cream and croutons.

title: oven baked drumsticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a bowl.
Dip drumstick into butter.
Roll in flour mixture to coat. Arrange in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake, uncovered, about 50 minutes.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let simmer, may use crock-pot.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix and add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and make 1-inch balls.
Put on cookie sheet and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes, onions and garlic; mix together and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add baking powder and eggs; mix well.
Add powdered milk and mix well.
Add the flour and mix all together.
If the batter is too thin, add a little more flour.
If batter is too thick, some milk.
Drop by big spoonfuls on heated frying pan with some of the shortening.
Fry pancakes to a golden brown.
Add more shortening to the frying pan each time you fry a new batch.
Fry the pancakes on medium heat or they will burn before they are cooked through.
Serve hot with applesauce or sour cream.
Makes 35 to 40 pancakes.

title: quick quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and then crumble.
Line a 10-inch pie shell with unbaked pie crust.
Arrange crumbled bacon or ham on bottom of pan.
Combine Scramblers, milk and pepper.
Pour over cheese and bacon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted 2 inches from edge comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: mississippi mud cake(alabama mud cake)
directions: Combine butter and cocoa in a medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat until butter melts. Remove from heat. Transfer to a large mixing bowl. Add sugar and eggs; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Add flour, salt and vanilla. Beat until blended. Stir in pecans.

Spoon batter into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows over hot cake. Immediately spread frosting over marshmallows on cake. (Chill before slicing for neater squares.)

title: holiday frosted fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water and juice of lemon.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add drained pineapple, diced bananas and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat egg whites with the cream of tartar and salt in a mixer bowl until frothy. Add the sugar gradually, beating constantly until stiff peaks form. Stir in 1/2 tsp. vanilla and pecans. Spread evenly in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack. Melt the chocolate into the water in a saucepan over low heat. Let stand until cool.
Fold in the whipped cream and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Spoon into the cooled pie shell.
Chill, covered for 2 hours or longer.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients together.
Add to other ingredients which have been mixed in mixing bowl.
Last of all, add the hot water.
Be certain to do this as mixing earlier does not produce the same result.
This bread is a nice change from all the sweet fruit cakes at holiday time.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water. Cook to soft-ball stage (238 degrees). Add peanuts and salt and cook to hard-crack stage (288 degrees); stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter. Add soda; stir vigorously until foamy. Pour at once into greased pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain.
Saute onions in butter; add beaten eggs.
Mix broccoli, flour, 1/2 cup bread crumbs and Cheez Whiz. Mix eggs, water, butter and sauteed onions.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup bread crumbs and bake at 350°.

title: yellow velvet cake
directions: Mix with mixer.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Line well buttered baking dish with crushed cornflakes.
Add tuna, pimientos, peas and margarine.
Pour soup on top of mixture, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well. Blend in chocolate, melted and cooled, and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition (5 minutes after 2nd egg) with electric mixer on medium speed. Turn into baked pie shell and chill 2 hours at least.
Serve with whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put butter and sugar in top of double boiler. Add 1 1/2 cups milk and heat over boiling water until milk is scalded.
Mix the flour and cocoa in 1/2 cup milk, then stir this mixture into contents of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into eggs.
Add eggs and vanilla to hot mixture.
Stir until thick.
Pour into pie shell. Cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Brown in oven at 350°.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and oranges together.
Add cottage cheese and stir.
Pour dry orange jello over everything.
Stir well.
Add Cool Whip and fold in.
Pour into oblong dish and refrigerate.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Spread Fritos in an 11 x 13-inch (approximately) baking dish; set aside.
Saute onion in cooking oil.
Add meat, soups, milk and green chilies; mix well and heat.
Pour over Fritos evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Add cheese; return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: open house punch
directions: Mash bananas in blender with small amount orange juice. Combine in large container remaining orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice, water and sugar.
Add banana mix; mix well.
Pour into containers that fit into punch bowl.
Freeze until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add sugar and oil to beaten eggs.
Add zucchini and vanilla and mix.
Mix dry ingredients and fold into zucchini mixture. Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour or until done.
Makes two medium-size loaves.

title: chicken breast cordon bleu
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Match pairs of chicken slices so they are equal size and shape.
Layer each of 4 slices of chicken with 1 slice cheese and 1 slice ham.
Top with matching slices of chicken, pressing edges to seal.

title: chicken stack-up salad
directions: In mixing bowl, combine chicken, curry, salt, paprika and pepper.
Toss to mix well.
In a clear glass salad bowl, layer lettuce, coated chicken, cucumber, macaroni and green pepper.

title: strawberry delight salad(diabetics can eat this!)
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Crush berries in a blender and add to gelatin mixture.
Add yogurt and sugar
substitute to the mixture and stir until well blended.
Pour into 4 individual molds and chill until firm.
Serves 4.

title: brisket
directions: Rub on	seasonings.
Cook
at 450° until brown (about 1 hour). Add
onion;
cover.
Cook 30 minutes per pound at 325° or until tender.
When
serving,
cut across grain.	For best flavor, marinate overnight.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, 1 cup of nuts and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in 1/2 inch granulated sugar and rest of nuts.
Store in airtight container.
Will ship well.

title: fig preserves
directions: Pour sugar over figs in a large container and let this set overnight in refrigerator.
Cook over low heat for about 3 hours or until syrup is thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Wash bell peppers and remove seeds.
Cut stems off hot peppers.
Put peppers in blender (fine grind).
Pour through colander, saving 1/3 cup of the liquid.
Combine liquid, water and remaining ingredients in pot and boil hard for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Certo.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Remove scum from top and add food coloring.
Pour in jars and seal with paraffin.
Can be eaten with meat or on crackers with cream cheese.
Makes 12 (1/2 pints).

title: curried chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, Mandarin sections and celery.

title: homemade strawberry banana ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, mash berries, banana, lemon juice and nutmeg with potato masher to a slightly chunky puree.
Stir in ice cream until well blended.
Transfer to freezer container.
Cover and freeze at least 4 hours until firm.

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Melt Crisco and margarine.
Pour over Pepperidge Farm herb mix.
Toss until coated.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet (do not cover).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Blend in pizza sauce and garlic salt.
Mix together all ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle cheese.

title: moon balls
directions: Mix milk, honey and peanut butter together until well blended. Chill. Form into marble size balls and roll in crushed cereal or wheat germ.

title: really difficult banana pudding recipe
directions: Mix pudding, milk, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together in a large bowl.
Layer pudding, bananas and crushed wafers.

title: it's good, it's easy salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in a dish.
Then sprinkle dry Jell-O on top.
Let set, then serve.

title: pecan crisp(quick treat)
directions: Place graham crackers on foil lined cookie sheet.
Cover them with the chopped pecans.
Make a syrup of the butter or margarine and the sugar.
Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes, until it gets thick and changes color.
Pour syrup over the graham crackers and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut and cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place broken bread pieces in pan. Top with cheese.
Beat eggs lightly and add to milk.
Pour over cheese and bread.
Sprinkle cooked sausage on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 30 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pan pie
directions: Mix all together. Put in ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peas with rosemary and pine nuts
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute pine nuts until golden.
Add green onions and saute 2 minutes.
Add peas, rosemary and sugar to skillet and continue to cook until heated through. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add diced apples.
Add flour which has been sifted with soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add nuts.
Mix and place in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or dust top with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin and ice cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well in big bowl.
Pour into 2 deep pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° and bake for additional 30 minutes on bottom rack.
Top when cool with whipped topping.

title: vidalia onion salad
directions: Thinly slice the onion and tomato.
On 2 salad plates, alternate slices of onion and tomato. Drizzle with oil and vinegar. Sprinkle with basil, salt and pepper. Top with Parmesan cheese. Serve with warm French bread.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Drain veggies and blot dry on paper towel.
Sprinkle equal amounts on top of cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces.
Discard ends.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: 6  cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve and enjoy.

title: sugar coated potato doughnuts or doughnut holes
directions: Beat well eggs. Beat in sugar and shortening. Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and mace or vanilla. Sift together and stir in potatoes. Chill dough for 2 hours. Heat fat while rolling and cutting doughnuts. Fry until brown. Drain over kettle, then on absorbent paper in warm place. Serve plain or sugared. To sugar, put white powdered sugar in a paper bag and shake the doughnuts.

title: garbage snack mix
directions: Mix peanut butter and almond bark.
Pour over cereal mix. Spread thin on cookie sheets; let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Mix sugar, 1 quart water and cinnamon sticks in a 6-quart pan. Boil for 5 minutes.
Then add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade juice and 1 1/2 quarts water.
Set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter baking dish and fill with apples, water and cinnamon. Mix together the remaining ingredients with fingertips until crumbly.
Spread over apples and bake at 400° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: texas tortilla bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large skillet or Dutch oven, stirring until meat crumbles.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and next 5 ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Set aside.
Place crushed tortilla chips in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon 2/3 of beef mixture over tortilla chips.
Spread cream cheese evenly on one side of flour tortillas and sprinkle evenly with chiles.
Fold in half and arrange on beef mixture.
Spoon remaining beef mixture on top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake 5 additional minutes to melt cheese, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: sugar bear squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and peanuts; toss to coat well.
Press firmly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store in cool place.
Makes 24 squares.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Let broccoli thaw and drain.
Mix everything together, except buttered bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Heat beans, soup and tomatoes; add to meat mixture.
Cover bottom of large casserole with layers of tortillas, then layers of meat mixture, until full.
Top with slices of cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven until cheese bubbles.

title: bacon-cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble into pie shell.
Arrange shredded cheese over bacon.
Beat eggs slightly with both milks and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted 2 inches from edge comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole - mrs. nixon's
directions: Mix all together except potato chips, cheese and almonds. Refrigerate overnight in a 2-quart casserole.
Next day, cover with potato chips, cheese and slivered almonds.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil the chicken. Cool and strip the meat off the chicken bones.
Put tortilla chips on bottom of baking dish and place a layer of meat over the tortilla chips.
Mix together the onion, Ro-Tel, soups and chicken broth.
Pour a layer of mixture over the chicken, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat; layer of chips, chicken, broth mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave english muffin bread
directions: Grease 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Sprinkle with corn meal.
Shake out excess.
Combine milk and water.
Heat in microwave on High about 3 to 4 minutes (between 120° to 130° on thermometer).
Mix 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Add warm milk mixture and beat well.
Blend in remaining flour and stir until dough is stiff.
Knead in bowl.

title: marinated beef brisket
directions: You will need 1 large turkey-size oven bag.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute bell pepper, onions, jalapeno and paprika in 3/4 to 1 stick oleo.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until paste is cooked (about 10 minutes).
Add raw shrimp and cook until done. Do not overcook.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes, then add alternately milk, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.

title: french bread dip
directions: Cut top off bread and hollow out inside and lid.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add alternately.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Do not open oven for at least 1 hour.
Check cake after 1 hour.
May need another 1/2 hour.

title: konafa dessert(egypt)
directions: Heat shredded wheat on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Crumble 3 shredded biscuits in greased 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with almonds.
Add remaining crumbled cereal.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cereal with almonds. Let stand at room temperature 2 to 3 hours.
(Serve with ice cream.)

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in bowl.
Add salt, sugar and flour. (If mixture is too sticky, add some more flour.
If too dry, add some water.)
Make 8 small balls from dough.
Roll into long strips; shape into pretzels.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: 5-star champagne punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill.
Float slices of lemon and orange. Serves 40 people a champagne glassful.

title: power soup(stew)
directions: Empty contents of soup can and beans (do not drain beans) into saucepan.
Add frozen vegetables of your choice.
Season to taste with Mrs. Dash seasoning.
Heat and simmer until vegetables are softened to your preference.
High fiber, low-fat, nutritious, quick and easy.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into an 11 x 7
x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with capers and Old Bay seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll calzone
directions: Let bread rise until doubled on side board.
Flatten to 12 inches long and 4 inches wide.
Place on cookie sheet.
Fill bread with other ingredients and wrap tightly.
Let rise 1/2 hour more. Brush with butter or egg.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Slice. Great to cook ahead and warm up or have cold.

title: senegalese(african curried egg soup)
directions: Put butter in 4-quart heavy Dutch oven.
Heat over moderate heat until butter melts and is hot.
Add onions, carrots, celery, apples and curry powder.
Reduce heat to low and cook 20 minutes, stirring until ingredients are tender.
Stir flour into butter mixture.
Stir with wooden spoon until mixture is bubbly and no trace of flour are left.
Remove from heat, mash vegetable and apples right in Dutch oven.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and 1 1/2 cups water.
Return to heat and bring to a boil on high, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low and cover Dutch oven. Simmer 45 minutes.
Skim soup several times with metal spoon. Place Foley food mill over a 3 or 4-quart saucepan.
Pour soup into mill.
Press vegetables-apple mixture through mill into saucepan and discard any residue in mill.
(If Foley food mill is not available, press mixture through a sieve, using back of wooden spoon.)

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Rinse berries under cold water.
Put sugar, cinnamon, cornstarch, water and salt in pot.
Stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Keep stirring.
Boil 2 more minutes longer.
Add berries and lemon juice.
Bring back to boil; cook until thick, 3 or 4 minutes.
If too thick, add a little water.
Good over pancakes or ice cream or could be used for shortcake.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Remove core from cabbage. Place whole head in a large kettle of boiling salted water.
Cover and cook 3 minutes or until softened enough to pull off individual leaves.
Repeat to remove all larger leaves (about 30).
Cut thick center stem from each leaf. Chop remaining cabbage.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick oleo together; set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick melted oleo. Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour and salt alternately with combined soda and buttermilk. Add candy mixture, then nuts and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 70 to 75 minutes.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Combine catsup, salt, brown sugar, dry mustard, vinegar, sugar and beans.
Fry bacon; drain.
Add hamburg and brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Flatten 1 can crescent rolls on baking sheet; bake until done.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix onions, celery, pecans, pepper and mayonnaise.
Crumble in cornbread.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together with juices.
Add instant pudding (dry); mix well.
Keeps for several days in refrigerator.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix instant pudding, milk and ice cream in blender.
Spread mixture on cake and refrigerate.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to a boil. Boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour mixture over other ingredients and mix well.
Drop on waxed paper and let cool.

title: aunt ann clouse's french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream well. Blend in chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beating the first egg for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Then add second egg; beat for another 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie crust or graham cracker crust.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Melt butter in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
