Layer the next 6 ingredients and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool slightly before cutting into squares.

title: cantaloupe salad cocktail
directions: Pare and cut cantaloupe; chill.
Combine peaches, honeydew melon and grapes with dressing.
Chill 1 hour.
Arrange cantaloupe wedges to form oval or circle and fill centers with fruit mixture. Serves 4.

title: steak soup
directions: Make white sauce using 2 of 8 cups of water. Add everything, except meat. Saute meat in 2 tablespoons of oleo. Drain off grease; Add to mixture. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, mix beef, eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls (coat with flour).
In a large skillet, over moderately high heat, heat oil and brown pepper and onion slightly.
Remove with slotted spoon.
In same skillet, brown floured meat balls.
Drain off excess fat.

title: peach peels for fried pies
directions: Mix well.
Let set overnight.
Cook slowly the next morning until peels are light brown.
They will not be thick.
Can in hot jars.

title: daddy's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
(Use mixer.)
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour; alternate with buttermilk and soda.
Add water and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour or longer.
Let cake cool.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is baking, mix sugar, milk and margarine together, adding beaten egg last.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
Punch holes in cake with handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour juice from pineapple over cake and then spread pineapple over cake.
Pour sauce over pineapple and refrigerate.
Cake will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: jello-cheesecake pretzel pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with pretzels and 3 teaspoons sugar. Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
In a bowl, combine the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Pour on top of cooled pretzels.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and garlic in a food processor until smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese and mix well.
Line a 2-cup small bowl with plastic wrap.
Add cheese mixture.
Pull up plastic wrap to form a ball.
Unwrap and roll in parsley when cheese is cold and firm.
Place on serving platter and refrigerate.
Serve with no fat crackers.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Wrap 1 teaspoon cheese dough around each of 24 stuffed olives, completely covering olive.
Freeze on cookie sheets, then put in freezer bag.
To serve, take out the number desired and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° until golden brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Serve warm.

title: ma ma g's coffee cake
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and pour into a floured 9 x 13 cake pan. Top with the topping mixture. (I usually make twice the amount of topping and fold half into the cake mix. The rest goes on the top.)

title: chicken supreme
directions: Lightly flour chicken and saute until golden.
Remove and place in baking dish.
Saute mushrooms and set aside.
Place ham and cheese over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: coconut orange jumbles
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and coconut.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, about 25 minutes. Cut into thick slices.
Place in mixing bowl.
In a cup, combine vinegar, mustard and black pepper.
Pour mixture over potatoes and toss to mix well. Cover the bowl and let potatoes stand for 30 minutes.
Add the scallions, capers, dill and parsley and toss.
Pour oil over the salad and mix gently. Refrigerate.
Bring salad to room temperature before serving. Serves 4.

title: fruit toast
directions: Cook 2 minutes and serve over buttered toast or English muffins.

title: doris' chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Serves approximately 10 halves of chicken.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Prepare noodles according to directions. Drain in large skillet. Blend soup, milk and sour cream. Cook, stirring constantly, until hot. Stir in noodles and remaining ingredients. Heat through. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: puree of pumpkin soup
directions: In medium soup pot, melt butter/margarine.
Saute onion and leek, stirring occasionally until soft.
Stir in pumpkin, chicken broth, salt and spices.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Puree the mixture in batches in blender for a smoother texture or in food processor fitted with metal blade.
Can refrigerate for 2 days.
May be frozen.
Return to soup pot and add half and half.

title: braised kielbasa and potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in large skillet. Bring to a boil. Cover. Simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: diabetic green peas oriental
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: flounder in orange sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small pan.
Cover and cook over medium heat until marmalade melts, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in onions.
Place fish in baking dish coated with pam.
Spoon marmalade mixture evenly over filets.
Bake at 400 for 10 minutes until fish flakes when tested.
Single serving.

title: tamale soup
directions: Dump all ingredients together in a large stew pan. Cover and simmer to taste.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Combine the rice, chicken, celery, onion, mayo or Miracle Whip and soup.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix the crushed corn flakes and softened butter; spread on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: snapped green beans
directions: Fry bacon lightly.
Add all ingredients to beans.
Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes or until done.
Season to own taste.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Measure All-Bran and milk into a bowl; stir to combine and let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until most of moisture is absorbed.
Add eggs and shortening and beat well.
Add All-Bran mixture to flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.

title: hot dog and potato casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and water.
In shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch) alternate potatoes with soup mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with sliced hot dogs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry-apple cider
directions: Combine strawberries, apple cider and lemon juice in container of electric blender; cover and process until smooth.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together adding cornbread mix last.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: apple ring waldorf salad
directions: Prepare gelatin following package directions; chill until partially set.
Pour a little gelatin into a 6 1/2-cup ring mold. Cut enough thin apple wedges to fit bottom of mold; lay edges with unpeeled side out around the outside edge of mold.
Chill until almost firm.
Dice remaining apple.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and fold into remaining ingredients.
Spoon atop first layer.
Chill until firm.
Pan size (6 1/4-cup ring mold).

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk. Bring to a full rolling boil.
Let boil about 2 minutes.
Whil still hot, add peanut butter, salt, vanilla and oats.
Do not cook. Mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: applesauce gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch Bundt pan.
Into a large bowl, measure all ingredients except confectioners sugar.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl. Pour batter into pan.
Bake gingerbread 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool gingerbread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on rack. Sprinkle top of gingerbread lightly with confectioners sugar, if you like. Makes 16 servings.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and 2 tablespoons flour, tossing to coat. Add 1 cup sugar and mix well. Place in a 2-quart casserole. Combine oatmeal, pecans, 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar. Add butter and stir well.
Spread this mixture over the fruit mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Garnish with pecans and cranberries, if desired.

title: crab or shrimp dip
directions: Only fresh suckers should be used and these be cleaned when caught or as soon after as possible.
Cut the fish into 2 inch pieces (leave in the backbone).
Pack dry into jars to within 1 inch of top.
Add 1 tsp. salt to each quart jar.
Do NOT add water. Put on cap, screwing band firmly tight.

title: oreo cake
directions: Quarter Oreos into fourths; set aside.
Sift flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter until soft.
Add vanilla and almond extracts and sugar and beat well.
Then add eggs, one at a time, until thoroughly incorporated.
On low speed, add dry ingredients in three additions with sour cream in two additions until thoroughly incorporated after each addition.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread pineapple evenly over bottom of pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix from box over cherries.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in small amount of water.
Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: hard candy
directions: Line
a
cookie
sheet with heavy foil; lightly grease. Butter sides of heavy 2 quart saucepan.
Add sugar, syrup and water. Bring
to
a
boil, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved. Cook over medium heat to 300° on candy thermometer (hard
crack). Remove
from
heat, add flavoring oil and food coloring immediately.
Pour	onto prepared pan at once.
When candy begins to harden around edges, cut into bite size pieces with shears. Coat lightly with powdered sugar.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 pounds.

title: mandarin orange and onion salad
directions: In a large, nonmetallic container with a lid, combine mandarin orange segments, onion slices and poppy seed.
In a bowl, combine olive oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and white pepper.
Pour oil mixture over orange mixture.
Toss to coat oranges and onion. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Tear lettuce (choose one lettuce or a combination of several greens) into bite size pieces; add to the mandarin orange mixture.
Add avocado, if using.
Toss well and serve immediately.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Place butter in pan and melt in oven.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Place fruit in pan and pour batter over fruit. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: low calorie, low-fat brown rice pudding
directions: Rinse brown rice in cold water and drain well.
Combine the rice and water in a small saucepan and bring to a boil, covered. Simmer until water level drops to the top of the rice.
Remove from heat and let stand for 20 minutes.
Whisk remaining ingredients except nutmeg in a cold, stainless or enamel saucepan. Place over low heat and bring to a slow boil.
Mixture needs to be stirred continuously to prevent from browning on bottom.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.
Fold in brown rice.
Spoon into cups. Garnish with nutmeg.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute peppers in butter until soft.
Add corn, egg, pimientos and half of the can of onions, crushed fine.
Blend all together well.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil and drain noodles as instructed on package. Place in large bowl and place in refrigerator to chill. When ready to serve; add remaining ingredients. Toss and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in iron skillet like cornbread.
If you don't like it real sticky, use 1/2 can cream style corn and 1/2 can whole kernel corn.

title: easy peanut butter cookies(children can make)
directions: Combine all four ingredients with a spoon.
Chill mixture for at least an hour before baking.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Roll into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Press slightly with a fork to flatten.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: creamy broccoli cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in medium bowl.
Serve with assorted crackers or vegetable dippers.

title: party vegetable sandwiches
directions: Mix gelatin in water and let stand.
Use blender, adding 1/2 cup of water, to chop all ingredients.
Drain off water.
Mix mayonnaise, gelatin and all chopped vegetables, salt and lemon juice.
Let stand for at least 1 hour.
Makes enough spread for 2 loaves of bread.
You can freeze it if you want.
This is delicious.
Great for showers or a wedding.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk together; add Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crusts and chill 1 hour.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetables with dressing
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix all of the ingredients and cover.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: moussaka(greek main dish, wonderful)
directions: Brown onions, then potatoes, then meat (take out each; put aside brown next), then put tomatoes and garlic on toothpick.
Add bay leaf.
Sprinkle sage, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix together in a quart jar the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Add alternately onions and cucumbers, adding a pinch of salt and pepper after each layer.
When jar is filled, cover top and shake.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.
They will hold flavor and texture for 10 days to 2 weeks.

title: party punch
directions: Freeze mixture.
To serve: 1/2 glass mixture and rest with 7-Up.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add pectin and boil hard 1 minute. Stir in food coloring.
Pour into hot clean jars to within 1/2-inch of top. Screw on tops firmly.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes about 5 (8 ounce) jars.

title: nell's spinach dip in bread shell
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out a round bread loaf. Pour dip
inside
hollow.
Arrange
bread pieces around edge of loaf and use for dipping.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Place large skillet over medium heat; add butter and melt.
Add sliced onions and cook until softened and translucent (do not allow onions to brown).
Add the red cabbage slices, salt, sugar and sliced apples, stir to combine.
Add the two onion quarters stuck with cloves.
Pour in the red wine vinegar and red wine.
Cover and let braise over low heat until cabbage is soft and nearly all the liquid has been absorbed, about 1 1/2 hours.
Taste for seasoning.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick over medium heat, stirring well.
Pour into pie shell.

title: great baked beans
directions: Drain beans and put in baking dish.
Add sugar and pepper; mix.
Cut bacon in pieces and cook over low heat to bring out most of fat.
Do not brown.
Put bacon pieces on beans.
Bake in a 325° oven until bacon is brown and beans are bubbly.

title: oatmeal peanut butter bars
directions: Crumb oatmeal, sugar, butter and salt like a pie crust.
Add vanilla and syrup.
Stir with a spoon until all is coated and sticky.
Spread in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: mimi's carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Put into 2 (10-inch round greased pans).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost top and sides with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: perfect roast every time
directions: Brown all sides of roast to "seal" roast; season to taste, e.g. salt, pepper, garlic, etc.
Fill Dutch oven or roasting pan 1/2 full with water.
Add soups and stir.
Put in roast and cover. Bake for 3 hours at 350°.
You can add common or favorite vegetables while roasting.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder. Gradually add to creamed mixture with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add coconut, rum, lemon, vanilla and butter flavorings.
Mix well.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Leave cake in pan until completely cooled.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add applesauce and soda. Mix raisins, spices, nuts and salt with sifted flour. Add to applesauce mixture. Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: healthy stir-fry
directions: Brown steak in 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Set aside bowl. Cook broccoli, celery and carrots in 1 tablespoon oil until onion is clear.
Drain excess oil from pan.
Salt to taste.
Heat until hot.
Serve with rice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo and spinach; add dry soup mix, chopped chestnuts and onions.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Carve out round rye or pumpernickel bread.
Fill hollow with dip.
Serve with cubed bread chunks, crackers, veggies or bread sticks.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Beat in egg. Add butter and nutmeg.
Bake in a well-greased, shallow pan at 350° until brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and milk.
Bring to boiling, then add rolled oats, vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Stir.
Add cherries and stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: abigail adams' champagne punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in tea.
Add orange juice, lemon rind and juice and rum.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour rum mixture and champagne over ice in punch bowl.
Garnish with fresh orange slices and mint sprigs.
Makes 16 (4-ounce) servings.

title: coffee cake-filled
directions: Mix flour and oleo as for pie dough; add remaining.
Add this to flour, oleo mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, divide into 3 parts and roll and fill like jelly roll.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Separate crescent dough into 8 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Combine cream cheese, mushrooms and salt, mixing well; may use blender or food processor.
Spread mushroom mixture in equal amounts over each rectangle of dough.
Starting at long sides, roll up each rectangle jelly roll fashion; pinch seams to seal.
Slice logs into 1-inch pieces; place seam side down on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush each log with egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in baked pie shells or graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat until well blended the sugar, eggs, margarine and milk. Stir in the bread cubes and pineapple.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top.
May be served hot or cold.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Beat sugars, oil and eggs together.
Sift flour, soda and powder together.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute okra in oil 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, onions, garlic and pepper. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add water, tomatoes and bay leaves; cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat
oven
Grease bottom only of 9-inch loaf pan. Mix
all
ingredients;
beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan. Bake 65 to 70 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
But since ovens differ, when pie begins to make your house smell real good, you better start checking.

title: vegetarian macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray 8-inch baking dish with PAM.
Layer macaroni in dish.
Spread cottage cheese over macaroni. Sprinkle on spices.
Then layer vegetables.
Add Mozzarella evenly over vegetables.
Pour chicken broth over entire mixture.
Spread on tomato paste.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: low-fat one cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and then refrigerate until time to serve.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Remove
core from cabbage.
Cook in boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes
or until leaves become loose and slightly limp. Drain. Pull
off
leaves.
Set
aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except the last 2.
Blend tomato sauce with chili powder.
Add
1/3 cup to mixture.
Fill each cabbage leaf with about 1/4
cup
of mixture.
Put near base of leaf.
Fold leaf base over filling.
Roll toward tip of leaf.
Fold outer edges of leaf
under.
Put
in
a
x
9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over cabbage rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade salsa
directions: In a large bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: 7 cups.

title: spinach tortellini soup
directions: Saute oil, garlic, onion, celery and basil for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in broth and beans.
Cook 9 to 12 minutes.
Stir in tortellini.
Continue cooking until tender.
Garnish with fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring water, cocoa and butter to a boil in saucepan. Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl. Pour boiled mixture over combined mixture and mix well. Bake in sheet pan for 20 minutes at 400°. When baked, ice with frosting.

title: breadfort collins, colorado
directions: Add all ingredients except flour.
Mix together.
Add flour. Knead.
Let rise for about 45 minutes.
Knead again and put into greased pans and let rise in warm place about 65 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine cornbread, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and sage; set aside. Place on medium heat until boiling. Pour over bread mixture; add eggs and mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: mandazi kenyan doughnuts
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in egg and milk.
Roll out to about 3/4-inch thickness on a well floured surface.
Cut in triangles or with biscuit cutter before frying.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown in large skillet the hamburger, onion and bell pepper. Drain off any liquid.
Add tomato sauce, taco seasoning and corn. Mix well.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix the soda and buttermilk; let stand while mixing candy. Melt the candy bars and syrup over low flame or in microwave. Cream together the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and Hershey mixture to creamed oleo-sugar mixture.
Sift the flour; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add the vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° in a tube pan.
Let cool for a while, then turn out of pan and cover while warm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, Cool Whip, salt and curry.
Add celery, grapes, chicken and almonds.
Mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease a baking dish.
Fill; top with more cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Soak crackers in milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Add rest of ingredients to cracker mix.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Use 2 (8-inch) pans.
Good with Easy Custard Frosting.

title: linda golden's salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir in milk slowly; cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir small amount of milk mixture into egg yolks, stir back into milk mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Mix confectioners sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle 2/3 mixture in pie crust.
Add the rest of peanut butter mixture to filling and pour into pie crust.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven at 325°.

title: easy pie crust
directions: In pie dish or pan, mix flour, sugar and salt.
Combine oil and milk.
Whisk briefly.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix with a fork.
Then pat into dish to form crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° until done.
Fill as desired. Makes 1 pie crust.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops in oil.
Spread kraut over browned pork chops.
Top with sour cream and paprika.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes, until pork chops are tender.

title: creamy lemon pie(yields 1 pie)
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand and ReaLemon.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped topping of your choice.

title: vanilla extract
directions: Add the vanilla beans to the vodka and close tight.
Let stand 2 to 3 months.
The vodka mixture will turn amber colored.

title: tofu fried like eggs
directions: Tofu needs to be sliced and mashed up in pan.
Add all ingredients.
Cook until liquid is gone.
It takes the place of scrambled eggs.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in 1 1/2 cups water to which 3/4 teaspoon salt has been added for about ten minutes.
Drain and add next five ingredients.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish and put 1 cup of stuffing in the bottom.
Add squash mixture; top with remaining stuffing and dot with butter.
Also sprinkle with almonds if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fried rice with chicken
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix the soy sauce and pepper in a small bowl; set aside.
Place chicken in a medium bowl and add 1 tablespoon to chicken.
Mix well to marinate.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add eggs; stir to cook until done.
Make sure eggs are separated.
Remove and put on a plate.
Set aside.
Add remaining oil to wok or skillet.
Add chicken; stir-fry until fully cooked. Remove; put on plate and set aside.
Cook onions, carrots and peas in wok or skillet; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Leave in wok or skillet.

title: aunt kathleen's banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, sour milk, mashed bananas and vanilla. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes; makes 24 cupcakes, or at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: diabetic spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in the water until water is cooked out.
Cool. Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener, oil and vanilla; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to applesauce mixture.
Mix well. Bake in loaf pan sprayed with Pam for 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine lard and boiling water.
Let cool.
Add the 1/8 cup warm water, the yeast and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Let stand until yeast is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients except almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and sprinkle almonds on top and return to oven for 5 to 7 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: nutcracker brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in chocolate syrup.
Stir in the flour (batter will look curdled).
Pour the batter into prepared pan. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven or until toothpick inserted in center of brownies comes out clean.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until almost done.
Drain.
Coat baking dish, 9 x 13-inch, with butter.
Add vegetables.
Stir in cheese, milk and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add onion rings and bake another 10 minutes.

title: no-roll white sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Press down with a glass which has been dipped in sugar. Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.

title: crock-pot barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken, salt and barbecue sauce in crock-pot.
Turn on low.
Cook slow all day and it is ready when you get in from work.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, garlic salt and onion in a bowl.
Add enough boiling water to moisten.
Add mixture of egg and milk.
When adding water, it will foam up, do not add too much.
Drop from teaspoon into hot fat and fry.

title: cranberry torte
directions: First Layer:
Melt 1/3 cup oleo; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
(Save some for top.)

title: patty melt
directions: Combine beef, salt and pepper and mix lightly.
Shape into 2 patties.
In a greased heavy frying pan, grill hamburger patties over medium-high heat 4 to 5 minutes per side for rare and 6 minutes per side for medium.
Add vegetable oil to pan and then onions.
Saute onions until soft and golden brown.
Top 2 slices of bread with hamburgers, then with onions, a slice of cheese and remaining slices of bread.
Lightly butter outside of sandwich and grill on a griddle or in a heavy frying pan until brown on both sides and cheese is melted.
(If you prefer, you can make sandwich with rye toast and melt the cheese under a broiler.)

title: egg casserole supreme
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt and cool butter and add to eggs.
Mix in baking powder and flour and stir until they dissolve.
Add the can of cheese soup (undiluted).
Grate cheese and add to egg mixture. Add pepper.
Saute bacon; drain and crumble.
Saute 1/2 pound sausage; drain all fat off.
Saute mushrooms and drain.
Add any or all you'd like.
Blend into egg mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°. (You can prepare the night before, refrigerate and bake the next morning.)

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and cover well.
Place bowl in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days, but re-mix again once each day.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together 1 egg in 1/2 cup water and vinegar. Mix flour, salt and sugar together and cut in shortening. Stir egg mixture into flour mixture. Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: peanut butter mud pie
directions: Follow directions for pudding mix.
When pudding is chilled, put puffed rice in a large bowl.
Add peanut butter and honey; mix well.
Pour pudding over rice mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: boiled cookies
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to rolling boil and cook for one minute (until a drop forms soft ball in cold water).
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper. Let cool.

title: hawaiian lemonade
directions: Add 1 can water to frozen lemonade concentrate.
Add apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Serve in 12 ounce glasses that have about 1 cup chilled ginger ale and ice already in the glasses. Trim with lemon slices.

title: holiday asparagus
directions: Thaw asparagus; drain well and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well and set aside. Layer half of asparagus, water chestnuts, mushrooms, pimento, egg and soup mixture in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Cut up fruit, what you like and dip as you eat.

title: green bean and pea salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables (use a large bowl; it makes quite a bit).

title: all in one stew
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except biscuits.
Cook until mixture is hot.
Separate biscuit dough and place on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: eggnog pudding(excellent for special occasions and holidays)
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/4 cup water.
Heat half of eggnog to near boiling.
Add gelatine; stir until totally dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar; stir, then add rest of eggnog and sherry.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: turkey strata
directions: Combine turkey, 3/4 cup cheese, celery, olives and salt.
Mix lightly.
Place bread cubes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with turkey mixture and remaining bread cubes.
Combine all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 10 servings.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, salt and nuts and mix well.
Shape into walnut sized balls.
Place balls on ungreased baking pan in 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Roll in powdered sugar and cool; roll again in sugar.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, strawberries, milk and eggs with spoon, then beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan and ice.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: creole seafood seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Store in a air tight container.
Great on Fish, Poultry and Pork.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: devonshire sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into a sausage and wrap in tinfoil.
Steam for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine and cook onions until tender.
Spray casserole with Pam; line bottom with cracker crumbs.
Add onions and soup in layers until dish is full.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with broccoli.
Top with crumbs (bread, cracker, potatoes chips or whatever) and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pot lickin apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon, nutmeg, and food coloring. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat milk to boiling.
Then in a large bowl, mix the sugar, Crisco and salt.
Next, crumble the yeast cube in warm water.
Mix the egg in with the milk.
Stir milk and egg into large bowl along with water and yeast mixture.
Combine all ingredients well.
Roll out dough and spread butter on it.
Sprinkle cinnamon all over butter dough.
Roll dough into a large log; cut 3 inch slices off end.
Lay on cookie sheet.
Bake them for 20 minutes at 300°.
Let cool.
Eat warm!

title: mama's chicken
directions: Bake chicken at 375° for 45 minutes.
When cooled, remove meat and dice.
Set aside.
Next in bowl mix soup, celery, almonds, salt, onion, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add diced chicken and pour mixture into a buttered casserole dish.
In a small bowl, mix potato chips and cheese, then sprinkle over casserole evenly. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked banana squash
directions: Cut squash pieces into about 4 x 6-inch pieces.
Brush melted butter evenly inside part of the squash.
Sprinkle nutmeg and 1 tablespoon brown sugar over each piece of squash.
Place in shallow pan in oven.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour both cans into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Pour yellow cake mix evenly over the top.
Pour melted margarine onto cake.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together; spread mixture on 6 to 10 medium flour tortillas.
Roll up.
Toothpicks will hold them together. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into slices.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover cookie sheet with rolls.
Press seams together to form large crust.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes in 375° oven.
Mix together Miracle Whip, cheese and dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust. Spread finely chopped vegetables on top and press into cheese mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cut into small squares.
Serve as an hors d'oeuvre.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: crumb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, using eggs, oil and water.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: never fail chocolate fudge
directions: Place
sugar,
canned
milk
and butter in large pan on stove. Bring
to	boil,
stirring
constantly, for 6 minutes. Remove from
heat.
Immediately
add
Hershey bars, chocolate chips and other ingredients.	Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: roasted pig's stomach
directions: Remove the inner lining of the stomach and discard.
Wash stomach well and then soak in salt water several hours.
Drain and fill stomach with filling.
Sew securely.

title: creamed pea sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt and stir in cooked peas.

title: diane's french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and sifted dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in muffin tins.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens.
Take 4 or 5 tablespoons of mixture and add to the egg yolks.
Blend together and add to the other mixture.
Add butter, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Cook 2 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Soften cheeses and combine in large bowl; beat until well mixed.
Add chopped garlic and 2 cups chopped pecans and mix well. Place in fridge for a few minutes.
Tear off large sheet of Saran Wrap or foil.
Place on table and sprinkle with chili powder and remaining nuts.
Form balls or logs and roll in paper with chili powder and nuts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Whip eggs.
Add sugar slowly and beat until stiff.
Add whipping cream, one cup at a time, beating well between cups.
Be careful not to beat until it is butter.
Blend in vanilla, salt and milk.
Pour into ice cream bucket and plug in your freezer or call the children to help in turning the crank.
Enjoy!

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all and chill.
Before serving, garnish with more nuts.

title: spaghetti-gratin
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Put in al dente cooked spaghetti with parsley and oregano.
Slice tomatoes over spaghetti.
Sprinkle basil on top.
Grate cheese; sprinkle on top, then sprinkle crumbled bacon and chopped onions.
Pour heavy cream over entire mixture.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Put in preheated 350° oven.
Bake 20 minutes until heated through and cheese is melted. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine together.
Beat eggs and powdered sugar together.
Add melted mixture to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator 1 1/2 hours.
Cut before it sets too firm.

title: fresh tomato pie
directions: (You can use lemon pepper seasoning instead of salt and pepper.)

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion. Add water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil. Add broccoli and simmer for 5 minutes. Add milk and Velveeta.
Simmer until melted on low heat, stirring frequently.

title: tacos
directions: Put the beef in a pan and you fry it for 30 minutes.
Put the cheese in a pan you fry it.
Take the tortilla, and then you put in the ingredients, like the beef, the cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Then you shove it in your mouth and eat it.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine enchilada sauce mix, tomato sauce and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Set aside.
Combine 1/2 of each cheese in a medium mixing bowl. Add sour cream, 1 cup green onion and cumin.
Mix well.

title: chicken broccoli cassorole
directions: Bring frozen broccoli to
boil
in salted water; drain. Saute celery and onion
in
oleo,
then
mix
all
ingredients together, adding chicken last.
Bake in casserole dish in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo in top of double boiler.
Cool thoroughly and add marshmallows.
Divide dough into 2 parts, form rolls and roll in powdered sugar and coconut on wax paper.
Store in refrigerator until firm.
Slice into desired thickness.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° in glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store at room temperature, lightly covered.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Grease 9-inch square baking dish or pan.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: dill pickles
directions: Scrub very small cucumbers and cover with ice. Let stand for 4 hours. Drain and put into sterile jars. For each quart jar, add 1/8 teaspoon alum, 3 cloves garlic and 2 heads dill.

title: refrigerator biscuit dough
directions: Mix
flour,
baking
powder, salt, sugar and shortening until well blended.
Refrigerate.
When ready to make biscuits use 1 cup mix and 1/3 cup milk.
Roll or drop and bake.

title: steak and spinach slices
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Score both sides of steak by making shallow cuts in a diamond pattern. Pound with a meat mallet until meat flattens to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Mix together spinach and cheese; spread mixture on steak.
Sprinkle with garlic.
Roll steak in jelly roll fashion, beginning at short side.
Skewer meat roll with toothpicks 1 inch apart.
Cut meat roll into 8 one inch thick slices.
Place slices on a cookie sheet coated with nonstick spray.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes for medium doneness.

title: popcorn pastels
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place popcorn in a large 4-inch deep buttered baking pan.
Keep warm in oven.
Cut two large pieces of wax paper to fit on 2 cookie sheets.
Lightly butter the wax paper. In a larger saucepan, combine the sugar, corn syrup, butter, salt and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly then cook without stirring until mixture reaches 250° on a candy thermometer.
Stir in gelatin powder and continue cooking for about 1 minute until mixture reaches 260°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda quickly but thoroughly.
Remove popcorn from oven and pour syrup mixture at once while foamy over popcorn.
Mix gently to coat.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Turn out onto wax paper.
Cool completely, then separate into small pieces. Store in tightly covered containers.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
Add 1 cup 7-Up, drained crushed pineapple, marshmallows and sliced bananas.
Chill until firm.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 9 ingredients.
Shape into small meat balls.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Place meatballs in oil.
Cover and cook slowly.
Turn meatballs occasionally.
Drain oil.
Mix chili sauce and grape jelly in skillet; heat until blended.
Add meatballs, cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes about 20 meatballs.

title: quick fried rice
directions: Heat wok with 1 tablespoon oil added (large skillet may be used).
When wok is hot, add broccoli slaw or cabbage.
Cook until heated through, but still crisp.
Add a teaspoon of soy sauce, mushrooms, water chestnuts and onion.
Stir and add rice.
Stir thoroughly and add soy sauce until desired salt flavor is reached. Pepper to taste.
Cooking time after all ingredients have been added is 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cut tomatoes,
peppers and onions in small pieces.
Put in large
pot.
Boil
about 30 minutes; add sugar and vinegar. Boil for another hour, stirring occasionally. When ingredients have thickened, pour into jars and seal.

title: country casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and drain fat.
Brown onion and green pepper.
Add to browned beef.
Add beans, macaroni and juice.
Mix well.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Drain, combine and toss with dressing.

title: chicken-dinner on the grill
directions: Prepare coals in grill for a medium heat.
Lay out 4 pieces of aluminum foil large enough to hold 1 breast and 1/4 vegetables. Remove skin from breasts, if desired, and place one in center of each foil.
Spread each breast with about 1/2 teaspoon of mustard. Clean vegetables and quarter, then place equally around chicken. Season all and wrap tightly in drug store wrap so there is no leakage.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients over Crispix cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Pour into a plastic bag and toss with powdered sugar until chocolate is covered.
Store in airtight container.

title: rolls (brown)
directions: Mix sugar, bran, salt, and shortening.
Add hot water.
In another bowl pour lukewarm water over yeast.
Beat eggs separately and add to sugar bran mixture.
When cool, add yeast to the mixture.
Add flour which has been sifted.
Put mixture in refrigerator.
When it has doubled in size, it is ready to make rolls.
Let rise thoroughly.
Bake in hot over 400° - 450°.

title: crab dip
directions: Put softened cream cheese in middle of round or oval shaped plate.
Flatten and shape.
(Leave edge for crackers.)
Pour on bottle of cocktail sauce.
Smooth and spread around.
Put the crab meat all over the top.

title: banquet punch
directions: First quart of sherbet should be softened.
Blend the orange drink with the soft pineapple sherbet in your punch bowl.
Float second quart of sherbet in your punch bowl.
Pour needed drink over the floating sherbet.
As you need more punch, add orange drink or sherbet as needed.
Serves 45.

title: christmas scent
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Keep simmering, add water as needed.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Best if put in flat baking dish.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together thoroughly sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in sour milk and banana.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and soda.
Add walnuts and pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Toothpick inserted in center will come out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes, then wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In large heavy skillet over medium heat, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Saute onion and bell pepper about 3 minutes.
In large bowl combine onion, bell pepper, salmon, bread crumbs, salt (if desired), black pepper and eggs.
Stir gently to mix.
Form mixture into 8 to 10 small or 6 medium-sized patties.
Dredge in coating until lightly covered.
In same skillet, heat oil for pan frying until hot; add croquettes (do not overcrowd).
Fry patties until cooked through and golden brown, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Place in baking dish.
Chop cheese into small pieces and place over broccoli.
Crumble crackers over cheese; pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mt. hope brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well and pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: light rolls
directions: Warm potato water, sugar and honey.
Add milk, yeast, salt and 3 cups flour.
Beat eggs and add butter and Crisco.
Mix in large bowl.
Stir in more flour to firm dough.
Knead and let rise twice.
Form rolls, buns or loaves.
Bake at 425°.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until slightly thickened. Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes until mixture will mold.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup melted oleo.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch or 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup oleo and pecans.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In baking dish, place amount of sliced beets you would like. Then add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Butter chips on top. Use juice also.
Thicken and bake.

title: carrot spice cake
directions: Blend sugar with oil or applesauce and oil.
Beat in eggs all at one time.
Sift together baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice, then pour into mixture.
Stir in carrots, pecans and pineapple.
Turn into greased and floured cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tests done.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package (do not add salt).
Cook until most of water is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° until hot.
Top with canned onion rings.
Freezes well.

title: candy nut drops
directions: Heat the morsels in a double boiler until melted.
Add the crushed noodles and the nuts.
Stir until well coated with morsels. Drop on wax paper by the teaspoonful and let cool.

title: 7 day cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar and salt over cabbage, peppers and onions and let stand for 1 hour. Stir and drain some of the liquid.
Combine oil, vinegar, celery seed and dry mustard.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Chill.
A small jar of diced pimentos makes a more colorful salad.
Keep refrigerated.
It will be good for a week!

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt oleo and cheese.
Stir in powdered sugar; stir.
(Add 1 ingredient at a time.)
Add cocoa, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into pan.
Let set in refrigerator to cool for a few hours, then cut into squares.

title: fried hot water bread
directions: Mix slowly until cornmeal is absorbed.
Spoon meal mix into wet hands.
Shape into pones.
Drop into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Let drain on paper towel.
Serve with vegetables or fish.

title: cheese cake
directions: Lay one package of croissants in a 9 x 11-inch cake pan. Press together with fingers. Whip cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together until smooth. Spread on croissants. Separate and lay second package croissants on top of cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: forgotten cookies(night time cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar, then vanilla. Fold in morsels and nuts. Grease cookie sheet well. Drop mixture by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Place in oven and turn oven off. Leave until next morning. Do not open oven door to peek. Oven has to be completely cold.

title: chow mein noodle cookies(no cook chocolate)
directions: Melt chocolate bits in double boiler.
Stir in noodles and peanuts until covered all over.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Cool.
Pack between plastic wrap.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Coat a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan with vegetable oil. Lightly dust with flour. Toss 2 tablespoons of cake mix with the chocolate chips and nuts. Set aside. Place remaining cake mix, dry pudding mix, sour cream, oil, water, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl. Beat on low speed with an electric mixer for 1 minute. Scrape down sides and bottom of bowl and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Fold in the chip and nut mixture. Pour into prepared pan and bake about 50 minutes until cake springs back when touched lightly. Remove from oven and let cool on wire rack 10 minutes before inverting onto the rack to finish cooling.

title: ole-time yummy beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat in 2 tablespoons hot shortening, turning often.
Add 2 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients. Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add vegetables (may need to add a little more hot water).
Cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pie filling and vanilla in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat in oven until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Mix Bisquick, sugar, milk and margarine with fork until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
If desired, stir in 2 tablespoons chopped nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot cherry mixture.
Bake until topping is light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
You may also sprinkle a cinnamon-sugar mixture on top. Serves 6.

title: ugly cake
directions: Spread coconut on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.
Mix cake as directed on box and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and margarine together.
Drop in spoonfuls on top of cake batter. Twirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: joyce's chicken
directions: Gently brown chicken in 1 tablespoon of the oil.
Remove.
Add remaining oil.
Saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 4 minutes longer.
Stir in green pepper, tomatoes, tomato paste, chicken broth, wine, basil and black pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer gently 25 minutes longer.
Serve sprinkled generously with parsley.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 375°.
Mix apples, flour, sugar and spices.
Pour mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Dab with butter and pour the milk over the apples; place top crust on.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 375° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Boil until mixture thickens, cool.
Mix with the next six ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: plantation cheese log
directions: Blend all ingredients, except chili powder.
Shape into 2 rolls (7 x 1 1/2-inches).
Sprinkle chili powder on waxed paper. Roll cheese log in chili powder, coating evenly; chill.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form into a ball.
Let harden.
Place on serving dish and cover with cocktail sauce.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 30 muffin cups with foil baking cups.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Melt Cheddar cheese in the microwave in a large bowl.
Add Bisquick and sausage. Mix well. Roll into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread with lemon and walnuts
directions: This recipe is made in a food processor but probably can be made by hand just as well.

title: ginger cookies(old recipe)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses and buttermilk.
Mix flour, soda and ginger.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll and cut as desired.
This makes a large amount of cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Put cream, sour cream and dry taco mix in blender or mix with electric mixer.
Pour sauce in 12 x 16-inch cookie pan.
Add shredded lettuce, onions and cheese, placing tomatoes on top. Serve with taco chips.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl in order given. Place on floured board and roll to pencil thickness. Cut into 2 or 3 inch strips. Drop into boiling salt water. Cook until they float to top.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until almost tender.
Peel and shred potatoes.
In large bowl, mix potatoes, cheese and margarine until margarine is melted.
Stir in rest of ingredients except paprika. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: jailhouse chili
directions: Cook chili meat until gray.
Add water and simmer 2 hours. Mix spices together and stir into meat.
Simmer 30 minutes more. Mix flour and meal with water to make a thin paste.
Stir into chili and cook about 20 minutes more, stirring often to prevent sticking.

title: nice and spicy dressing
directions: In a small saucepan, combine apple juice, vinegar, garlic powder, cornstarch, oregano and spices. Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Pour into a small bowl. Cover and chill until ready to use. Beat with a wire whisk before serving.
Makes about 1 cup.
One tablespoon contains less than 1 gram
of fat and .2 milligrams of sodium.

title: triple bean salad
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix last 3 and pour over vegetables.
Cover and set in refrigerator at least 8 hours. Toss several times.

title: rice consomme
directions: Melt margarine and cook onions until tender.
Add other ingredients and pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: busy-day-dinner-in-a-pot
directions: Brown pork chops
in
Dutch
oven
in
bacon drippings. Remove and set aside.
Saute
onions
for	a minute or two and then add cabbage.
Lay
potatoes on top of cabbage, then layer of pork chops.
Salt
and
pepper to taste. Add 1/2 cup water. Put lid on and
let simmer for 20 minutes or until cabbage and potatoes are done.
Serves 4.

title: mammie's yellow cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and blend thoroughly.
Sift salt, baking powder and flour together.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately.
Add vanilla and blend by hand or mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured pans (three 9-inch pans).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until cake starts to leave sides of pans in 350° oven.

title: texas braggin' chili
directions: Saute beef and chopped onion.
Add chili powder and comino seed.
Saute a few minutes.
Don't burn!
Add tomato paste and mix well, then add tomato juice or V-8 to make soupy.
Next, add beans (optional) and bouillon cubes.
Simmer several hours, stirring occasionally.
Heat should be low enough so the mixture bubbles now and then.
Serve with a scoop of rice on top and side dish of crushed jalapeno or red pepper for twang.
The longer you cook it, the better it gets.
Serves 10 normal chili-heads, 6 Texans.

title: mary's chili
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Use large pot.)
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir all ingredients together except blueberries.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Spray muffin tin and fill 3/4 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: country style steak "gluoish"
directions: Put hamburger patties in electric frying pan.
When brown, add onions and pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Cook until all are done.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup and 1 cap water.
Stir until smooth.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and miracle whip, mix until well blended.
Add the other ingredients and mix.
Chill mixture before molding.
To mold, drop by teaspoon around a glass.

title: brie, crackers and grapes* * * * *
directions: Doris is an old dear friend from Missouri.
She gave me this recipe so many years ago I don't remember when.
I'm sure it isn't exactly like it was then, but I served it to my Sicilian neighbors and they told me it was the best they had ever had.
Here again, the homemade noodles are better.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add peanut butter.
Blend in dry ingredients; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Place Kiss and press into cookie until the cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven 2 to 5 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: barge rice
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve with chips as a dip.
Can also be served as a main dish over extra rice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate 4 hours.
Serve with vegetables.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate, coffee and rum extract; mix well.
Stir in flour and chopped walnuts.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Press
evenly
in pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over crust mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: creme de menthe delight
directions: Crush the Andes candies (easiest to do when chilled).
Mix pudding with 3 cups of milk and beat for 1 minute.
Stir in crushed candies.
Chill.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Separate wings at joints.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour on chicken.
Cover and refrigerate, turning chicken occasionally, at least 1 hour.

title: make ahead 'n knock 'em dead cake
directions: Note:
Better to use a 13 x 9-inch pan with plastic cover, especially with refrigerators that are frost-free.

title: gourmet cheese spread
directions: Mix cheeses, onion and pepper together with enough mayonnaise until the consistency is spreadable.
Let set for a while before serving.
(The longer it sets, the more the flavors mix.)
Serve with any type of cracker.
Yummy!

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, butter and 1 egg and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: vegetable lasagne(yields 8 servings)
directions: Cook lasagne according to package directions for 10 minutes; drain.
(Separate lasagne and lay flat on wax paper or foil to keep the pieces from sticking together as they cool).
Saute mushrooms, carrots, onion and garlic in oil in 5-quart saucepan until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add spinach and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine cottage cheese and eggs; add to spinach mixture.
Pour a thin layer of sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange layer of lasagne over sauce.
Spread half the spinach mixture over lasagne; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of Parmesan. Repeat layer of lasagne, remaining spinach mixture and 1 tablespoon of Parmesan.
Top with remaining lasagne and sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover; bake 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting for easier handling.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken with raspberry sauce
directions: Pan brown chicken pieces in butter.
Finish in roasting pan in a 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan; pour off juices.
Deglaze pan with raspberry vinegar.
Add raspberry jam and chicken stock.
Simmer until thickened.
Add fresh raspberries; remove from heat.
Place warm chicken in serving dish, then pour sauce over all.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate swirl cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, 1 teaspoon soda and salt.
Add with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Combine syrup and 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Measure 2 cups batter into small bowl; blend in syrup mixture.
Add coconut to remaining batter.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Pour chocolate batter over vanilla batter in pan; do not mix.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Glaze or frost as desired.

title: potato pancakes(yester years)
directions: First, grate potatoes and onion together on grater.
Add your eggs and flour with potatoes and onion.
Mix well.
If batter is too loose, add a little more flour (to your own judgement).
Cook in oil.
Mazola oil makes them crispier.

title: slush fruit punch
directions: Mix jello and sugar; add boiling water and stir until jello is dissolved.
Add lemonade and water.
Place mixture in a container suitable for freezing.
When ready to serve, allow to thaw about 4 hours.
Add Sprite.

title: cabbage bundles
directions: Remove outer leaves from cabbage head and steam in salted water for about 5 minutes or until leaves are flexible.
(Save inner head of cabbage for other uses.)
Drain and cool leaves. Saute onion and ground chicken until slightly browned.
Add cooked rice and seasonings.
Drop a tablespoon of mixture on the stem end of a cabbage leaf.
Roll into bundles and fasten with a toothpick. Place bundles in baking pan or casserole dish and pour undiluted soup over them.
Bake in a 350° oven, about 45 minutes.
If desired, sour cream can be added just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: In a large pot, put cranberries, water, pinch of salt and sugar.
Cover pot while cooking and cook until the cranberries pop! Add cherry Jell-O, celery, nuts, grapes, pineapple and coconut. Mix well and put into greased mold.
Let jell overnight.
Remove from mold.
Perfect for Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add milk.
Mix.
Add butter, bring to a boil.
Hard boil for 3 minutes.
Stir while cooking.
Remove from heat and add 2 c. oatmeal, 1 tsp. vanilla, 2/3 cup peanut butter.
Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: tempura
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients and mix until smooth. Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Mix well with blender or with mixer and refrigerate.

title: sausage bake
directions: Put a layer of sausage, a layer of potatoes and a layer of onions.
Pour tomato soup with spices over onions and cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 2 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: 1. Cream together cheese and sugar (in large bowl).

title: tangy onion flowers
directions: Peel onions.
Cut 1/2-inch slice from top of each onion.
Leave root end; cut each onion from top into 8 wedges to within 1/2-inch of root end.
Gently pull wedges apart.
Brush onion with vegetable oil.
Place onto 12-inch aluminum foil square.
Sprinkle onion with vinegar, oregano, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Wrap foil securely around onion.
Cook on medium heat (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Boil water for noodles.
Add pasta.
Cook until tender. Meanwhile, cut pepperoni, cheese, cauliflower, broccoli and carrots into bite-size pieces.
Cut olives in slices.
Put in large bowl and add dressing; set aside.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Melt margarine; let cool.
Spread 1/2 crumbs on bottom of 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over crumbs.
Layer berries next.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Add remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.
Suitable for freezing. Frozen berries will make it more juicy than fresh.

title: fish newburg
directions: Stir butter and flour to make a paste over low light.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Boil until thick.
Remove from stove. Add grated cheese, sherry and cooked fish.
Return to stove, preferably over double boiler.
Cook a few minutes and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Serve immediately.

title: french market doughnuts
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and cool to warm. Sprinkle yeast on the 2 tablespoons warm water to dissolve. After milk has cooled, add oil, eggs and dissolved yeast.
Blend with wooden spoon.
Gradually add flour, beating well.
Cover with wax paper, then towel.
Let rise until doubled.
Turn soft dough onto well floured board and knead well, but gently.
Roll out to 18 x 12-inches and cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Cover again with towel and let rise 30 or 40 minutes.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until golden brown (takes about 1 or 2 minutes to brown).
Drain on paper towels and while warm sprinkle on sugar or shake in paper bag.
Use plenty of confectioners sugar.
This doughnut does not taste like our regular doughnuts.

title: apricot nut salad
directions: In saucepan, place apricots with enough water to cover.
Bring just to simmer; reduce heat and simmer, covered, until apricots are tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain, reserving liquid.

title: grandma's english trifle
directions: Slice pound cake into nine pieces.
Line the sides of a 2-quart glass bowl with jam.
Spread cake pieces and fill the center also with cake pieces.
Prepare pudding.
Pour over cake; chill.

title: banana squares
directions: In small bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks and mix well.
Add bananas.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Garnish with whipped cream and banana slices.

title: puttin' on the ritz chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Cool and cube.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and pour into glass casserole dish; add chicken.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and chicken soup.
Pour over top of chicken. Crush Ritz crackers and pour over top of chicken.
Pour remaining 1/2 stick oleo over crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: salad dressing for slaw or salad
directions: Blend together well. Pour over combination for salads or slaw when ready to serve. Chill.

title: squash pickle
directions: Combine squash and onions; sprinkle with enough salt to cover. Set 1 hour.
Drain off liquid.
Mix vinegar, sugar, seeds and pepper.
Bring to hard boil.
Add squash and onions.
Bring to boil again.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Place zucchini in colander.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 30 minutes.
Squeeze as much liquid as possible from zucchini with your hands.
In medium skillet, cook onion in butter over medium heat about 3 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Transfer zucchini and onion to a large bowl.
Stir in eggs, flour and pepper.
Pour cooking oil into medium skillet.
Heat over medium-high heat.
Drop slightly rounded tablespoonfuls of batter into hot oil and flatten with back of spoon.
Cook pancakes until golden, turning once.
Repeat until all batter is used.
Serve with tomato sauce as side dish.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In medium size saucepan over medium heat, combine rice, 1 1/2 cups milk, sugar and Sweet One.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes or until thick and slightly creamy.
Beat remaining 1/2 cup milk and egg; stir into rice mixture.
Stir in raisins. Without letting mixture boil, continue cooking 2 minutes.
Stir in margarine and vanilla (mixture will thicken on standing).

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: In skillet, on medium heat, cook butter and chicken 10 minutes, until browned on both sides.
Remove and set aside. Combine soup, cheese, water or wine and ham; heat to boiling. Add chicken.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 5 minutes. Serve with egg noodles.

title: holiday green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Pour in bean mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together; simmer until heated through. Serves 6.

title: tina's easter treats
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, peanut butter and margarine.
Add noodles and M&M's.
Dip 1/3 cupful onto a greased cookie sheet. Form into a nest.
Let firm, usually overnight works well.
Dip the bottom of each nest in powdered sugar after it firms.
Take and put about 3 peanuts on each nest.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a shallow dish, layer the refried beans, then the mashed avocados.
Mix together the sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over the bean mixture.
Next, sprinkle on the green onions, tomatoes, black olives and shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: freezer to oven steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place a sheet of aluminum foil in a shallow baking pan. Arrange frozen steaks in a single layer, not touching.
Spread each steak lightly with the mustard.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Arrange onion in a single layer in pan and brush with oil.
Wrap foil loosely over meat to make a tent.
Set timer for 30 minutes.
When timer goes off, steaks are ready for those who like them rare.
Add another 5 minutes for medium-rare and 5 more minutes for medium.
Separate onion rings before serving.

title: chocolate-macaroon squares
directions: In a food processor or with your fingers, whirl or rub the butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 cup flour until the dough begins to hold together.
Press evenly over bottom of a 9-inch square pan. Bake the crust in a 350° oven until golden, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red apple cake
directions: Cream together oil and egg.
Add chopped apples.
Slowly add dry ingredients.
Fold in dates, cherries and nuts.
Add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: fallen fudge cake
directions: Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish in 350° oven. While butter melts, combine sugar, flour, cocoa, vanilla and milk together.
Pour this mixture over melted butter.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and stir until melted.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla, then flour and baking powder.
Add nuts and chocolate morsels.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut candy into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: treet or spam sandwich filling
directions: Mash or grind the meat and eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
This will fill 6 hamburger buns or makes 6 sandwiches. Other additions to the filling can be 1 cup grated cheese, small amount of green pepper, onion or celery.

title: easy steak and rice
directions: Trim fat from steak. Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add steak and brown. Remove steak from skillet. Add remaining oil. Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring, until onion is tender and transparent. Return steak to pan. Add soy sauce, sugar and water. Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour or until steak is tender, adding more water if needed. Serve meat and pan drippings over rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old fashion rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, pudding mix, egg and raisins in saucepan. Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowl. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve warm.
Serves 10.

title: chili cheese
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Combine cheese, juice, garlic powder and pepper.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Stir in nuts.
Shape in a roll 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick.
Use wax paper.
Sprinkle with chili
powder and paprika.
Chill.
Before serving, let stand to soften.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef-broccoli pie
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add 1 1/4 cups of milk and the softened cream cheese.
Cook and stir until smooth and bubbly. Stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into the beaten egg; return to mixture skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened, 1/2 minute.
Stir in cooked, chopped broccoli; set aside.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix pineapple, brown sugar and mustard and put in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine other ingredients and put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake one hour at 350°.
To lift, cut into pieces and flip them so pineapple mixture is on top.

title: carrot carousel
directions: Pour 1/2 cup cold orange juice into blender container; sprinkle gelatin over.
Let stand 5 minutes; add boiling orange juice.
Process at low speed until gelatin is dissolved.
Use rubber spatula to push gelatin granules into mixture.
Add remaining cold orange juice, salt and mayonnaise; blend well.
Add carrots; cover.
Process at high speed until carrots are finely grated; stir in undrained pineapple.
Pour into 6-cup mold; chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon texas sheet cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 375° for 22 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown chopped onion in a small amount of butter.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
In a saucepan, melt oleo, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture; stir well.
Add buttermilk with baking soda, eggs and vanilla.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° on a greased sheet pan.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Cook broccoli and drain. Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
May be made ahead, frozen, then baked.
Makes a large amount.

title: strawberry bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Cool and then slice with a thread crosswise to make 4 layers.
Place 1 slice in bottom of bowl (like small punch bowl or salad bowl).
Mix first box of pudding according to directions on box and spread on top of cake in bowl, then place strawberries on top of pudding, then a layer of Cool Whip on top of strawberries.
Continue doing this until all layers are stacked.
The last one should have a layer of Cool Whip on top.
Eat and enjoy!

title: patriotic pops
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, combine the lemon juice, lime juice, water, sugar and corn syrup. Cook, stirring frequently, until the sugar dissolves, about 3 minutes. Transfer the mixture to a bowl and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Divide the mixture among 3 small bowls. Add a few drops of red food coloring to 1 bowl and stir. Add a few drops of blue food coloring to another bowl and stir. Return the plain and blue mixtures to the refrigerator.
