Divide the red mixture among the pop molds, cover with the lid, insert wooden sticks and freeze for 2 hours. Remove the lid, divide the plain mixture among the molds, cover and freeze for 3 hours.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers; remove seeds and cut in strips 1/2-inch wide. Cover with cold water and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Pack upright in sterilized jars.
Boil vinegar, water and sugar 3 minutes.
Add salt and pour over cucumbers.
Seal.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and keep in refrigerator.

title: peppermint ice-cream pie
directions: Crust: In medium mixing bowl, stir together oats, coconut, and nuts.
Set aside.

title: mom's toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Combine butter or shortening, granulated sugar, brown
sugar,
vanilla
and
water;
beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Add
flour mixture;
mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by well-rounded half teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie
sheets.
Bake
at
375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes one hundred 2-inch cookies.

title: holiday scent and punch
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil; simmer 30 minutes.
Refrigerate.
When you want to use it as a scent, simmer on stove without a cover.
Doubles as a holiday punch.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Have marble slab cold and greased with oleo.
Place sugar, syrup, hot water and paraffin in deep saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is well dissolved.
Add peanuts and continue cooking, stirring occasionally to 295° to 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add soda all at once. Immediately stir vigorously until soda is well distributed.
Pour onto marble slab and let cool.
When candy is cold, with knife, turn whole slab of candy over.
With knife handle, break into pieces.
Store in airtight container and keep in cool place.

title: creamed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, water and sugar in saucepan.
Simmer lightly covered about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain juices into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 3/4 cup mix with flour and nutmeg until flour is dissolved.
Add to carrots along with butter. Bring to boil and simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
If desired, garnish with parsley.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Freeze.
Thaw punch until mushy.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up before serving.

title: biscotti cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape dough like loaf of bread.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet until golden brown, about 12 minutes.
Cut like bread when cool.

title: corn and shrimp chowder
directions: Fry pork until crisp.
Remove from grease and pour off all but 3 tablespoons.
Add next 5 ingredients and cook 5 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add water and potatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Add corn, milk and shrimp.
Heat well, but do not boil as milk will curdle.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add pork.

title: barbecued corned beef
directions: Break beef apart.
Mix all ingredients except beef.
Add beef and cook over low heat for about 20 minutes.
Serve on warm buns.

title: light eggplant parmesan
directions: Generously coat cookie sheet with baking spray.
Cut eggplants into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Dip in egg, then coat with crumbs, combined with Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven about 10 minutes; turn.
Top each eggplant slice with a slice or two of fresh tomato; sprinkle with a little garlic powder and some Italian seasonings.
Bake 5 to
8 minutes.
Top each vegetable stack with a slice of cheese and bake until it melts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: swiss steak(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Cut meat into 4 pieces.
Trim fat.
Omit flouring and pounding meat.
Brown meat in hot oil.
In 3 1/2 to 4-quart crock-pot, place onion, celery and carrot. Sprinkle with thyme, tapioca, salt and pepper.
Pour undrained tomatoes over vegetables.
Add meat. Cover, cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours.
Serve with hot rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Gently mix all ingredients until thoroughly combined.
Cover and refrigerate.
Best if prepared day before use.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt in a small bowl; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, lightly beat egg white.
Add pecans; stir until coated.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over pecans; mix well. Spread in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove nuts from baking sheet while warm to cool on waxed paper.
Yield: About 6 cups.

title: dried beef chicken
directions: Cover bottom of large shallow casserole with dried beef.
Place chicken breast on the beef; place a piece of semi-fried (limp) bacon on each piece of chicken.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup and spread over the casserole.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato "mash"
directions: In a baking dish, combine the yams (drain them first).
Add pineapple, but do not drain.
Add margarine and 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Mash all ingredients into a smooth texture.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Blend and bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Top will brown.

title: hot fruited cabbage
directions: Saute apple and onion in 2 tablespoons oleo for 10 minutes. Add cabbage and water.
Cover and steam 20 minutes.
When tender, add sugar and vinegar.
Just before serving, add the last tablespoon of oleo, salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: light fruitcake
directions: Coat nuts
and fruits with 1/2 cup flour.
Cream butter, sugar,
eggs,
flavorings
and
3 cups flour.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Pour brandy over cake dripping slowly.
Cool on rack.
Wrap cake in cheesecloth.
Put in a tight container, store in cool place for 3 weeks,
adding a little brandy weekly.

title: cheddar pecan spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill in covered container. Use as sandwich spread or on wheat crackers.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears and bring to a boil 2 cups juice (add water, if needed, to make 2 cups).
Dissolve Jell-O in the juice.
Put in refrigerator until partially set.
Blend pears and cream cheese in blender until creamy.
Stir in Jell-O and nuts.
Fold in 1/2 carton Cool Whip.

title: date sticks
directions: Beat egg yolks, add sugar, flour, baking powder, dates, and nuts, then add beaten egg whites, spread thinly, Bake on a greased pan at 325° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cut in strips roll in powdered sugar.
For large cookie sheet double recipe.

title: no-egg cornbread
directions: Mix whatever amount of cornmeal for the cornbread you want with enough mild or hot salsa or picante sauce to wet all cornmeal.
"Fry" in nonstick skillet with Pam spray or bake.

title: honey-mallow coleslaw(6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients except walnuts.
Mix lightly.
Chill. Stir in walnuts just before serving.

title: ellie's vegetable soup
directions: Brown the beef in the oil.
Add the onions, salt and pepper. Add the water, tomatoes and marrow or knuckle bone.
Simmer about 1 1/2 or 2 hours, then add the broth, carrots, celery, potatoes and tomato sauce. Cook on low until veggies are tender (20 minutes to 1/2 hour).
Add the barley and parsley. Simmer.
Add either more beef broth, tomato sauce or water, depending on taste. Serve with fresh sour rye bread!

title: herb-baked chicken
directions: Combine all spices and pineapple juice; brush or pour over all of the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and cook 25 minutes longer or until done.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cook Duncan Hines butter cake as directed.
In saucepan, put sugar and cocoa.
Stir in butter, milk and light corn syrup. Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set in cold water for a few minutes.
Stir in the confectioners sugar, vanilla and peanut butter.
When this mixture begins to thicken, pour and spread on the cake.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown onion, mushrooms and rice in margarine until golden. Add beef bouillon broth or consomme.
Pour in greased casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: chutney cranberry sauce
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until cranberries release their juice. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Chill before serving.
Will keep refrigerated in airtight container up to 2 weeks.

title: southern candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut yams crosswise into 1/4 inch thick slices. Place in large skillet. Combine the sugar, brown sugar, and nutmeg (optional). Sprinkle over sweet potatoes. Dot with the butter and add the water. Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to low and cover pan.

After about 20 minutes, check the potatoes to see if they are fork tender. If not, continue cooking for another 5 minutes. By this time, the liquid should start to form a syrup. Remove cover and continue cooking for another 10 minutes or until the syrup has thickened.

title: butternut squash
directions: Mix together. Put in an uncovered casserole dish at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add rest of ingredients and toss.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Mix together 1 egg, butter and cake mix until well blended. Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan which has been sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Blend remaining eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl. Bring to a boil the oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water. (Bring to rapid boil; stir all the time.) Pour this in the flour and sugar mixture. Add remaining ingredients and beat. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan 30 minutes at 400°.

title: moist chocolate cake - no eggs
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and cocoa together.
Add buttermilk and oil.
Stir until blended.
Boil coffee and stir in gently.
Mixture will be soupy.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add water and tomato soup.
Add dates and nuts, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Boil sugar and water together and cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix together and mix every half hour while freezing.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in square or oblong pan.
Add other ingredients by layers, pressing them down, instead of mixing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: country breakfast casserole(great for company)
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Place bread in pan.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine rest of ingredients together and mix well. Pour over bread and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix Wesson oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into sugar and form into balls coated with sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes (do not overcook).
Remove to wire rack.
Cookies will flatten and crinkle.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: baked tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in long pan and cover top and sides with softened margarine.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
No longer! During last 20 minutes, baste with wine with bouillon cube dissolved in it.
If using mushrooms, add these at last 20 minute interval also.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: snap bean and potato salad(fat-free)
directions: Cook or steam red potatoes until firm-tender (12 minutes in steamer).
Transfer potatoes to bowl.
Steam beans until tender; add to potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients to vegetables and gently toss to mix and coat.

title: chicken and zucchini parmesan(microwave recipe)
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and flour.
Toss zucchini in mixture and place in shallow 2-quart casserole with lid.
Add chicken and toss.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes or until chicken loses pinkness.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Place meat in large kettle.
Add onion, bay leaf, cloves, garlic salt and salt.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for approximately 4 hours or until meat is tender. Drain liquid.
Cool.
Trim excess fat.
Chill in refrigerator, then slice in thin slices.

title: shrimp with shallots and cream sauce
directions: Shell, devein, rinse and dry shrimp.

Heat butter in a large skillet over high heat until brown. Add shrimp and saute 2 minutes on each side. Remove from skillet and keep warm. Add chopped shallots; saute for 1 minute over high heat. Combine wine, salt, pepper, parsley and tomato paste.
Add to skillet and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add cream and thyme; boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and strain.
Divide shrimp among 4 plates and spoon on sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage and ground meat
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add sliced cabbage, water, salt and pepper.
Cover with a lid.
Cook about 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Serve with corn bread.

title: shrimp fritters
directions: Mix beaten egg with remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil in deep fat fryer.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl.
Float vanilla ice cream on top.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in the pan.
Mix dry ingredients and milk. Pour over margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over mixture. Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: paper mache
directions: Tear newspaper into small pieces.
Soak overnight in hot water.
Mix well and knead.
Add Flour Paste and mix well.

title: texas slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and cucumber; layer with sugar.
Set aside.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat lemonade for about 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon ice cream; beat until well blended.
Gently stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
If necessary, freeze until mixture will mold.
Spoon onto crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 55 minutes in a 325° oven.
Glaze.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat oil to 380°.
Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla to the dry ingredients.
Beat well with electric mixer until smooth.

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press into bottom of 10 x 10
x 3-inch dish to make crust.

title: banana pudding
directions: I use large coffee cup to measure.
Cook in pan set in a larger pan of hot water.
Add sugar to 3-1/2 c. milk and heat. Beat eggs.
Dissolve corn starch in 1/2 c. milk, and add to beaten eggs.
Add some hot liquid to this.
Stir, cook until thickens. Cool.
Add vanilla.
Put in dish the pudding, graham crackers, and bananas.
Sprinkle rolled graham crackers on top.

title: brussels sprouts soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and carrots. Saute 5 minutes. Transfer vegetables to bowl.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add Brussels sprouts and onion.
Saute 3 minutes. Stir in broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes. Set aside 3/4 cup cooked Brussels sprouts.
Puree broth mixture in blender and return to large Dutch oven. Gradually add milk to flour. Blend and pour into soup.
Add mushroom mixture, Brussels sprouts, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Simmer 10 minutes. Add parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Fix frozen fruit ring for punch bowl.
Mix, chill and serve. Serves 50.

title: tuna boat
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve in a hollowed out loaf of pumpernickel.
This is especially good with leftover baked chicken.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, corn, onion and mayonnaise.
Put in a baking dish and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with cheese slices.
Melt butter.
Crumble crackers in butter.
Spoon over top of cheese. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour gradually and with lowest speed of mixer beat until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese batter.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning onto wire rack.
Cool before slicing.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender until all mixed well.
Pour into pie plate and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Rub fingers with a little butter or oil.
Add cold water.
Roll about 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into small pieces and drop in stew.

title: harvest pumpkin loaf
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add pumpkin.
Gradually stir in dry ingredients, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Take out of oven and cool in the pan for 10 minutes; then remove and cool on a wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serve in pita bread.
Improves with age.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spray casserole with nonstick baking spray.
Mix all ingredients and pour into dish.
Dust top with ground ginger and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Great served with ham.

title: cherry dump salad
directions: Mix pie filling and milk well.
Dump other ingredients in and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pound cake(1958 recipe)
directions: Whip butter until creamy.
Beat in eggs and sugar alternately. Fold in flour and add vanilla.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 nice loaf.

title: baked french toast
directions: Spray with Pam 1 large and 1 medium Pyrex dish.
Cut up French bread into 1-inch slices and line dishes.
In a bowl, mix all other ingredients; season to taste.
Dip bread slices into mixture over slices.
Store covered in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, pop in oven and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dockside marina peanut butter pie(chesapeake city, md)
directions: Blend well and add topping.
Pour into crust and freeze.
Thaw before cutting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place the sliced apples into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon, salt and water.
Rub together the
flour,
sugar
and oleo until fine.
Spread this over apples. Bake
at
for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: high nutrition snack
directions: Sunflowers are a favorite snack for Russian people, as popcorn is for many Americans. A nutritious snack can be made by roasting 1 cup preferably organic hulled sunflower seeds in a skillet (use no oil).
Take care to shake the skillet and stir constantly so as not to burn the seeds.
Add 2 proportions of water to 1 of tamari* or soy sauce when the seeds are lightly brown, until fluid dries in skillet. Eat warm.
(Careful not to burn.)

title: chocolate cake
directions: In medium mixing bowl, cream together sugar and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla and mix well, then set aside.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cocoa.
Add flour mixture to margarine and sugar mixture, alternating between flour, milk and coffee.
Mix well.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tammy's stir-fry veggies
directions: You may also add mushrooms, corn and cauliflower.

title: french cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar in large saucepan, then add milks.
Cook over medium heat until thick and boiling at least 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour in baked shells and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: peanut-coconut pie
directions: An original recipe that has won several Fair ribbons in New Mexico.

title: homemade granola
directions: Mix brown sugar, oil and honey in saucepan. Heat until sugar is dissolved. Combine dry ingredients in a 9 x 13 metal pan. Pour sugar mixture over the dry mixture and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Let cool in pan. Store in airtight container.

title: baked chicken and rice casserole
directions: Remove any fat from chicken breasts.
Spray a glass 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Stir together rice, water and soups in baking dish.
Top rice mixture with chicken breasts and sprinkle dry soup mix over all.
Cover dish with foil and place in preheated 400° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Serve with green and/or mixed vegetables.

title: minnie loyd's vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onions in a small amount of cooking oil.
Drain.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot overnight.

title: grandma spalding's lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in hot water gradually and cook until thick.
Add to this mixture the egg yolks (beaten); stir in gradually and cook for 1 minute.
Blend butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind into the hot mixture.
Beat egg white until frothy and fold gently into the lemon mixture.

title: april's razberry salad dressing
directions: Whisk all ingredients together in a bowl until well blended. Refrigerate at least 1 hour for flavors to blend.
Serve chilled or at room temperature over a bed of mixed salad greens.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Slice unpeeled orange; remove seeds.
Place half cranberries and half orange in food processor until evenly coated.
(Do until all are chopped.)
Stir in sugar.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and sweetened condensed milk in a large bowl. Refrigerate 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients. Stir well and refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon patties
directions: Stir all ingredients with a fork.
Drop by tablespoon in skillet.
Use 1 tablespoon shortening or oil in pan to fry on low to medium heat until brown on each side.

title: apple-walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 medium-sized muffin cups or line with paper liners; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Add combined eggs, apple juice concentrate, butter and vanilla; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in apple and walnuts.
Spoon batter into prepared cups, filling each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand in pan on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Mix with other ingredients but use only 1/2 can of cheese soup.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with rest of cheese soup.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add 1 cup of flour and 2 eggs together until you use all the flour and eggs; beat 1 minute after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake at 325°.
After 30 minutes, check for doneness with toothpick.
Let cool in pan.

title: one-pot spaghetti supper
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Add seasonings; arrange spaghetti on top.
Pour water and tomato juice over spaghetti, moistening all the spaghetti.
Cover and bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes or until spaghetti is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes:
4-6 servings.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks; add milk.
Stir into flour mixture, blending well.
Cook over hot water until thickening, stirring constantly.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell; cool.

title: light and creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze for 4 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Arrange stalks of broccoli in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: warm clam spread
directions: Mix together.
Place in small buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes until light brown and bubbly.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
except
popcorn
and
boil 2 minutes.
Remove
from heat and stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda.
Spray
a large brown bag with Pam.
Pour popped corn in bag, then pour in cooked mixture.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes, then shake well; microwave another minute, then shake well.
Microwave for another 1/2 minute.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: In skillet, brown ground chuck and drain off fat.
Add meat with remaining ingredients (except jalapeno peppers) to crock-pot. Stir well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.
Before serving, stir in chopped peppers, if hotter flavor is desired.

title: rich chocolate cookies
directions: Melt butter, chips and condensed milk.
Mix flour and 1 teaspoon of vanilla into chips mixture.
Add nuts.
Spoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: mushroom stew
directions: Brown pork cubes in oil in a 6-quart Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to a boil and then reduce heat. Simmer 2 hours.
Add water if necessary during simmering.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ahead of time to allow blend of flavor. Use any fruit (strawberries, grapes and blueberries are great).

title: cola chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole. Mix together the next 4 ingredients. Pour over chicken, cover and bake on 350° oven for 35-45 minutes. Makes a great gravy to pour over rice or mashed potatoes. Can also used this recipe substituting boneless pork chops and cream of celery soup. Very good.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Place in baking pan.
Combine all liquid ingredients.
Mix and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken confetti
directions: Drop split chicken breasts into a sack with coating mix and shake to thoroughly coat pieces.
Bake chicken in 350° oven until done, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Place Carrots, Potatoes and Water in a saucepan; cover and cook over medium heat until the vegetables are tender.
Drain, reserving cooking liquid.
In a skillet, saute Onions and Garlic in Butter for 10 minutes.
Add Flour; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Place Carrots, Potatoes, Onion mixture, Salt and Sugar in a blender or food processor; cover and puree until smooth, adding reserved cooking liquid as needed.
Pour into a 3-quart saucepan or dutch over.
Stir in Milk and heat through.
Add Cream and Cayenne; heat through (do not boil).
Garnish with Paprika.
Yield 10 - 12 servings.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Combine rhubarb, apples and strawberries; spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over rhubarb mixture.
Set aside.

title: jo's pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs two at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flavoring. Add flour and salt last, mixing well.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Turn stove to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: melissa's crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers in a large bowl.
Stir in oyster crackers.
Let stand for one hour before serving.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain all vegetables, saving juice to freeze for use in soups later.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Keep covered.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: quick, fast easy dessert
directions: Cut cake into slices.
Top each slice with fruit and whipped cream.
Another variation is to cut the pound cake into half after it is partially thawed, layer it with strawberries and then a layer of whipped cream.
The top layer is then spread with whipped cream.
When an individual slice is cut, take a tablespoon of the fruit juice to top it off with.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt cheese.
Add mayonnaise/sour cream.
Add beans (drain one can completely, about half of the second can).
Mix together completely.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add topping of Ritz crackers (crushed) and margarine slices.
Bake additional 15 minutes.

title: yum yum
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted oleo and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine vanilla instant pudding with milk. Blend until thick, then add softened ice cream.
Fold in gently. Pour over crackers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crumble some Ritz crackers on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Stir in cereal.
Add milk, oil and eggs.
Blend until moistened.
Do not stir again.
Can be stored 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Fill lightly greased tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: impossible chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate. Place eggs, milk, margarine, vanilla, melted chocolate, sugar and baking mix in blender and blend on high 1 minute.
Pour into plate and bake about 30 minutes or until custard leaves no indentation when pressed lightly in center.
Cool before serving with whipped cream. Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: momma's spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over clean, fresh spinach.

title: holiday salad
directions: Keep in refrigerator. Freezes well.

title: quiche, quick and easy
directions: Place pie crust in quiche pan or pie pan.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Guaranteed every time!

title: hot artichoke dip made in microwave
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Turn at 3 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits or chips.

title: chocolate chip or m&m cookies
directions: In a large bowl, blend shortening and both sugars until well blended. Add eggs and milk; stir until well blended.
Stir in flour and baking soda until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips or M&M's (or both, if desired).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes until lightly browned.
(Longer if a crisp cookie is desired.)

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat.
Drain and add first 8 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Tear each tortilla into 8 pieces.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, make a layer of tortillas, then meat and other ingredients.
Do the same until all of mixture is used, ending with tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Mix milk and cream of chicken soup and pour over cheese. Bake for 30 minutes

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in top, about 30 minutes.
Yields 18 servings.

title: peach preserves
directions: Mash
peaches.	Mix
cup
to
cup of peaches and sugar. Let stand
overnight.
Cook slowly in a heavy pot until thick (a tablespoon of lemon juice is added while cooking).	Before putting in
jar, add 2 tablespoons of vanilla flavoring per 8 cups of mixture.

title: shrimp mold appetizer
directions: Bring soup to a boil.
Melt cream cheese in soup.
Add other ingredients and put in ring mold.
Chill.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: dilled apple and potato salad(low-fat recipe)
directions: Rinse potatoes but do not peel; cut each in half.
Place in saucepan; add water just to cover.
Cover and cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Add carrots and cook 10 minutes more, or until vegetables are tender but firm.
Drain and rinse gently with cool water.
Drain again and set aside to cool.
Cut potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix well.
Add potatoes and carrots to bowl and stir gently with a rubber spatula.
Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Add extracts and bake for 1 hour.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Heat chicken broth to boiling in large skillet; add chicken.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add undrained pineapple chunks, green pepper, red pepper, carrot, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir cornstarch into soy sauce until smooth; stir into skillet mixture. Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix well. Do not grease glass 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cake is done. Take big 2-prong fork and poke holes all over hot cake. Let cool 30 minutes. Dissolve 1 small orange Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water. Add 1 cup cold water. Pour slowly over cake (getting into all holes); cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In tall microproof cup, mix brown sugar and rum.
Add water to two-thirds full.
Cook on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until very hot, but not boiling.
Add butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Add cinnamon stick.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread frosting in the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, 1 egg and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Beat at low speed until blended; beat at high until smooth.
Spread filling over frosting.
In large bowl, combine all cake ingredients.
Beat at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour batter over filling.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tight container.

title: giovanni's of st. louis farfaline al salome(as served at presidential inaugural banquet of 1985.)
directions: Bring 4 quarts water (salted) to boil; add pasta and cook to desired doneness.
Drain and set aside; keep warm.
Saute salmon in butter for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until resulting sauce is creamy, but not dry.
Add to pasta and let stand for 1 minute to combine flavors.
Add heavy cream and toss gently, several times over 2 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese and again toss gently. Sprinkle pepper on top.
Serves 4.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Cut ripe avocado in half and remove seed.
Peel and put pulp through sieve.
Add the other remaining ingredients; blend well.

title: mary's chicken and beef
directions: Wrap chicken in bacon.
Line dish with chipped beef; place chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 2 hours.
Very rich and delicious.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Crush cranberries, then add all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: janice's taco salad dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning and a little water.
Set aside.

title: somen salad sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a jar and shake vigorously. Use as a salad dressing.

title: chicken in red wine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Mix together butter, tarragon, basil, parsley and shallots and smear over the top of the chicken pieces.
Pour red wine down the side of dish until it extends halfway up the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes, until browned and done.
Can be done ahead and refrigerated but add 15 to 20 minutes of cooking time, if cold.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix bread crumbs, milk, beef, salt and pepper together and form into small balls. Brown in frying pan and drain excess fat. Mix soup, milk, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce. Add soup mixture to meat balls. Bring to a simmer. Stir in sour cream and serve over cooked noodles.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat eggs, salt and vanilla; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in flour and soda.
Add oatmeal and stir well.
Stir in nuts or raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Beat one egg white until stiff; set aside.
Beat on egg yolk. Add melted butter, salt, milk and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk.
Fold egg white into flour mix.
Dip into cracker meal.

title: asparagus egg casserole
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk. Stir in cheese. Place 1/2 bread crumbs in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Place alternate layers of sliced eggs, asparagus and cheese sauce on bread crumbs. Cover top with remaining bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef in skillet with butter and chopped onions.
Add beans and stir several minutes.
Pour soup over this.
Add salt and chili powder and simmer 15 to 25 minutes.
Serve with boiled or baked potatoes or with rice.

title: pink champagne salad
directions: Cream and mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts and mix well.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread into two 9-inch square pans.
Cover with lids or seal with foil and freeze.
Remove from freezer 20 or 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into small squares.
Let thaw before serving.
Return the rest to freezer.
This can be made several weeks ahead.
It keeps well in freezer.
Makes a good fruit salad or use as a quick dessert.

title: "turtle" cookies
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Pat dough into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then sprinkle with pecan halves.
Melt 2/3 cup margarine with 1/2 cup brown sugar; boil one minute.
Pour over crust.

title: "tater" candy
directions: Boil potato until well done.
Mash small portion of potato with fork.
Add small amount of sugar.
Alternate potato and sugar until all has been mixed well.
Potato and sugar should have the look of bread dough when finished.
Sprinkle sugar on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Roll out thin, spread on layer of peanut butter. Roll into a log and cut into bite sized pieces.
Refrigerate awhile before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Flavor with lemon and a little nutmeg or flavor with 1 teaspoon vanilla.
This makes 2 pies.
Bake in crust.

title: lois's cherry jello dessert
directions: Combine and bring to bubble stage, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add 1 (10 ounce) can Coke; stir until foam goes away.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash and prick potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, until done. Scoop out potato pulp; set aside.
Melt butter; add flour and stir.
Cook 1 minute or until thickened.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 of bacon, 1 cup cheese and milk.
Cook until heated; add sour cream.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve with cheese, onion, bacon and chives sprinkled on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: herbed rice
directions: Heat water and bouillon cube.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Cook until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 14 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a strip of bacon.
Cover the bottom of a flat greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Mix the undiluted soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate about 3 1/4 hours before serving time.
Heat oven to 275° and bake, uncovered, for 3 hours.

title: luau ribs
directions: Mix together all ingredients except ribs; set aside.
Rub ribs on both sides with salt and pepper.
Place ribs, meat side up, in a foil-lined shallow pan.
Bake in a very hot 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Continue baking at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until done, basting with sauce several times.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine for 3 to 4 minutes.
Grate toasted bread to fine crumbs.
Add these and all other ingredients to crabmeat.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour milk evenly over mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add brown sugar and vanilla. Stir in pecan halves with a spoon.
Drop one by one on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned tomato soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Add thyme, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Stir this and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Make a paste with 6 tablespoons broth with flour.
Stir into soup.
Add rest of chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar and baking soda.
If serving right away, add 1 cup half and half.
If saving, freeze in a 2-quart jar.
Do not add half and half if going to freeze, it tends to curdle.

title: canape spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and add mayonnaise until desired consistency.

title: omelet deluxe
directions: In cooking oil, saute mushrooms gently over low heat.
Combine eggs, milk, onion and seasonings.
Add to the mushrooms and cook slowly.
As egg mixture sets, lift gently with spatula to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
Fold in half.
Garnish with shredded cheese and parsley.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: old fashioned cinnamon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix. Pour cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box.
Just before cake is ready to bring out of the oven, sprinkle top with the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Cut butter into small squares and let melt on top of cinnamon and sugar mix until it looks all done.
Let cool and the top of the cake will be crunchy.
Enjoy plain or with a scoop of your favorite ice cream.

title: dr. hudgins waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric beater.
Pour on griddle. Serve immediately with your favorite syrup.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, syrup and salt together.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter and Fluff.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool slightly and cut.
Cool completely, then enjoy!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large pot of boiling water, cook macaroni until tender according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly and place in large mixing bowl.
Stir in butter and egg, saving enough to sprinkle on the top of casserole.
Stir in cheese.

title: canning string beans
directions: Wash beans and sterilize jars.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast into water; stir in sugar and let sit for 10 minutes.
Add salt, oil and flour.
Make sure you add enough flour to be able to handle; knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let sit until double.
Punch down and shape into two loaves.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake about 35 minutes or until loaves sound hollow. Spread with butter while still hot.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in microwave, then stir.
Cook on high for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda (should be frothy).
Put popcorn in paper bag, pour mixture on top and shake.
Roll up bag, put into microwave on High for 1 minute.
Take out, shake, roll back up and cook for 1 more minute.
It is best not to use microwave popcorn.

title: bean sprout salad
directions: Wash sprouts and remove as much seed shell as possible. Drain.
Then pour some boiling water over sprouts in colander and drain well.
Dry them well quickly in paper towel or cloth towel.

title: crisp sweet slaw
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Whisk the vinegar, vegetable oil, Equal, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and pepper.
Pour over vegetables; toss to blend.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: peppy potatoes
directions: Pour coating mix into mixing bag.
Dip potatoes in melted butter; shake in bag.
Place potatoes on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: 1. Pour Chex| cereals into large bowl; set aside.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and saute onions until golden.
Add beef and basil; cook until browned.
Stir in green beans and tomatoes; then turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof casserole. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Stir buttermilk, sugar, pecans and salt into 5-quart dish. (Watch closely.
Mixture bubbles and boils over sometimes.
May use larger bowl, if you have one.)
Cook in microwave on High for 12 minutes.
(Stir at 4 minute intervals.) Stir in baking soda and continue to stir until foamy.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla; beat until tacky, about 3 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, chilies, salt and the 3/4 cup of cheese. Fold in chicken, onion and chopped up tortillas. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or more, until top cheese is toasty.

title: mary's date bars
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar.
Add all dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut into squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: hot rice cakes with turkey
directions: Preheat broiler. On stove, spray pan with Pam.
Heat over medium heat for 1 minute.
Add turkey, cumin and garlic; cook through about 2 to 3 minutes.
Spoon turkey onto rice cakes, top with remaining ingredients.
Broil for 2 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and condensed milk together.
Stir well. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Pour into a buttered, greased square pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and enough melted butter to hold together and press into baking dish.
Mix Eagle Brand, sour cream and lemon juice.
Pour into dish.
Spoon apple pie filling on top. Sprinkle with nuts and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma joe's cherry delight
directions: Crush crackers, mix in melted butter.
Spread into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes in 375° oven until cracker crust is golden brown.
Cool.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Boil this mixture gently for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool a few minutes.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons soda.
When cold, add 2 cups flour.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven until done, when cake tester comes out clean.

title: baked salmon cakes
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, mustard and steak sauce.
Pour the mixture over salmon, bread crumbs, parsley flakes, onion flakes, chives, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into patties.
Bake on a nonstick cookie sheet in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes. Turn over carefully.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: "poor man's" pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In the pie shell, place the brown sugar, flour and salt.
Mix with your fingers.
Pour the evaporated milk over the flour and sugar, but do not mix this in. Dot with butter and drift cinnamon liberally over all.
Bake for 50 minutes or until the filling just bubbles up in the middle.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Wet your fingers and spread cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake according to instructions on package until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Spread over cookie dough.
Spread glaze over the top of that. Decorate with fruit.
Chill.
Cut like a pizza when serving.

title: pasta pazool soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine celery, onion, garlic, parsley, tomato sauce, paste, tomatoes and macaroni.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, 1/2 hour.
Before serving, add lemon juice and cheese.

title: crab melt
directions: Mix all ingredients except muffins.
Spread on muffins. Broil, close to broiler, keeping an eye on them (about 1 minute) until brown and bubbly.

title: rice caliente
directions: Saute ground beef, onions and seasonings until done.
Drain off fat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes with rice.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Brown onions and celery in oil.
Blend in flour and broth. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add juice and all seasonings. Add chicken and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift sugar into stiffly beaten egg whites and beat well.
Add flour, sifted 5 times with cream of tartar.
Add vanilla.
Stir as little as possible after adding flour.
Bake in floured tube pan for 45 minutes.
Invert and let stand until cold.

title: light bread
directions: Mix hot water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Mix yeast in warm water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add flour to make a stiff batter.
Put in large container; let rise 2 hours in warm place.
Grease pans.
Stir in more flour until dough is stiff. Knead dough thoroughly.
Make into loaves or buns.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until done.
Makes several loaves.
Brush top with oleo.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in roaster and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
After first hour of baking, baste with brown sugar, dry mustard, water and vinegar.
Mix and bring to a boil before pouring over ham loaf.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple, Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Add marshmallows and pecans; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before eating.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Dough:
In a small bowl, combine warm water and yeast.
Stir. Add salt and sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add 1 cup flour and mix. Let stand, covered, 20 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large pot, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles and parsley. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Add noodles and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes longer or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: linguine salad
directions: Make dressing as shown on package.
Place quartered tomatoes, cucumbers and pepperoni slices in with linguine.
Pour dressing over linguine.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme over top mix a little. Refrigerate until cool.

title: jiffy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steaks in oil.
Cut in strips or squares.
Add mushroom soup, milk, sour cream, mushrooms, catsup and remainder of ingredients.

title: pete's sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine undiluted evaporated milk, oleo and sugar in saucepan; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes and continue stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chopped nuts, semi-sweet chocolate bits and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Add tomato sauce or tomatoes and 1 package of dry taco mix.
Put dough in pie plate and cover in layers, beginning with 1 cup broken corn chips, meat, onion and tomato mixture and sour cream.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Place in a large casserole dish. Add Stove Top stuffing (season packet and bread crumbs).
Add soup with 2 cups water.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: scrapple
directions: Mix
all
dry ingredients together in a large pan.
Mix oil, Worcestershire sauce and salts together and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix
well
to distribute the oil evenly.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: zangie cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then add sugar and vinegar.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon crisps
directions: Form cookies with cookie press.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll biscuits in mixture and place in a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle on nuts as you add biscuits. Combine brown sugar and margarine; heat until dissolved.
Pour over biscuits as icing.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Cook broccoli and rice; combine with all other ingredients except cheese.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with cheese spread and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions in a small amount of oil.
Brown meat in the same pan with onion.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Place yeast in large bowl.
Mix butter, milk, 1 1/4 cups water and molasses.
Pour over yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add salt, flours and raisins; mix thoroughly.
Place dough into 2 round greased casseroles; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Wrap each loaf in towel; cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix and set aside. Sift together dry ingredients and stir into pumpkin mix.
Add water.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add flour and nuts.
Lightly butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press crust into pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Saute carrots and onion in 2 tablespoons butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Stir in 1 cup stuffing mix, soup and sour cream.
Remove from heat.
Cook cauliflower in boiling water 10 minutes or just until tender.
Add to soup mixture.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish, which has been coated with cooking spray.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup stuffing mix; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: parsley dill dressing
directions: Mix well.
Use on salad or use as a dip.

title: mama's corn pudding
directions: Drain corn; place in a bowl.
In another bowl, place eggs; beat well.
Add milk and sugar.
Mix well.
Add corn.
Add salt. Place 4 pats of butter on top of corn.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until brown.

title: mexican chili dinner(taco dinner)
directions: Fry hamburger and onions until done.
Add kidney beans, tomato soup, tomato sauce, taco seasoning, Italian seasoning and oregano. Let this simmer for 1 hour.
In separate dishes, dice lettuce, Cheddar cheese, onions, peppers, celery, cucumbers, tomatoes and olives.
Create your own salad.
Arrange raw vegetables on plate; put hamburger combination on that, then sour cream, topped with lots of crushed Dorito chips and hot sauce.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat sugar and milk into cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in coconut.
Fold in cool Whip and extract.
Spoon into pie crust. Freeze until firm about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature about 15 minutes.
Freeze leftover pie.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg over peaches.
Toss to mix.
Place in a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and egg to a crumb-like texture.
Pour over peaches.
Melt margarine and drizzle over crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top turns slightly brown and crusty.
Serve hot or cold, plain or with ice cream or topping.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southwest chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth. Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients, except Ro-Tel tomatoes. Pour this mixture over the rice. Top with Ro-Tel tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: scrambled dogs
directions: Heat chili and boil wieners. In an oval dish, place a bun with a wiener in it. Score the wiener in bite-size sections. Add mustard, onions and pickles, if desired. Add jalapenos or hot sauce if you like it hot. Put cheese slice on top. Cover it all with chili. Put oyster crackers on top. Best eaten with a tablespoon.

title: spinach dip in a bread
directions: Mix salad dressing, sour cream and salad dressing mix until well blended.
Add spinach, water chestnuts and red peppers; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: fritos salad
directions: Toss all together and add dressing to taste.
Refrigerate leftover.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except sugar, vinegar and oil. Mix these together in boiler; heat until sugar is dissolved; cool. Add to vegetables.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: mama mere's yeast biscuits
directions: Mix milk, salt, sugar and lard together.
Put yeast and baking powder in a little warm milk and dissolve.
Mix all ingredients together; work in flour.
Roll out into biscuits on a floured surface.
Turn in lard; let rise and bake at 400° until golden.

title: spritz cookies
directions: You will need a Spritzo Maker.

title: cream cheese pie(frozen)
directions: Spread 3/4 of the crumbs on the bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Have cream cheese at room temperature; mix together with egg yolks, sugar and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Also whip cream.
Add both to first mixture.
Spread remaining crumbs on top of mixture and freeze 24 hours or more before serving.
I prefer using a glass pan.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain
pineapple; reserve liquid.
Mix sugar, flour and egg together;
gradually stir in pineapple liquid.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows and pineapple; mix well.
Put in serving dish and top with crushed peanuts. Refrigerate.

title: grandma caruso's spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, add olive oil and cook Italian sausage in it until brown.
Once cooked, begin adding onion, garlic, parsley, basil, oregano, Mrs. Dash, salt, pepper, cheese, sugar and red pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes (chop them up) and fill the can 1/2 full with warm water; add to sauce.
Add puree, paste and sauce and as you add these, fill each of their cans 1/2 full with warm water; add to sauce.
Stir.
Add your meatballs raw or precooked.
Cook on a low heat all day.
The longer it cooks, the better your sauce.
Stir frequently.
Watch carefully while cooking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: crock-pot stuffing
directions: Mix butter, onion and celery and saute.
Add mushrooms, spices and broth.
Add some of the hot liquid to egg while stirring, then add to broth.
Mix hot liquid into bread crumbs.
Put into crock-pot and cook on high for 45 minutes, then on low for 4 hours.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Scald fruit juice.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs.
Stir in fruit juice slowly.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thickened. When cool, add whipped cream.
Mix in drained fruit salad.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and put in prepared baking dish.
Cook for 35 minutes in 425° oven or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
In bowl mix and set aside both cans of soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Cook broccoli and add to soup mixture.
Mix in celery and onion.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and pat into a greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers(for two)
directions: Parboil peppers until color changes.
While pepper cooks, brown ground beef with onion until done.
Add rice to meat and add ketchup plus a few drops of Tabasco and mix well.
Drain and stuff pepper.
Add dollop of ketchup to top of each.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chinese rice ring
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Saute onions and pimientos in butter in frypan until softened. Stir eggs, salt and bean sprouts into rice.
Put in well-greased round ring mold.
Put ring mold on large baking or roasting pan filled with 1-inch water.
Heat in oven about 20 minutes and unmold.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (3-inch) muffin pan cups. Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and oregano.
Set aside. Combine soup, milk, eggs, oil and zucchini.
Mix well. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Batter will be lumpy. Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling almost full. Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean. Serve warm.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: In 3-quart glass casserole, combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Cook on Medium-high for 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened; stir twice during cooking.
Slice potatoes and add to thickened sauce.
Cook on High 17 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender; stir once during cooking.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Make hole in center of mixture and pour all liquid ingredients into hole.
Mix by hand. Grease and flour two 8 x 4-inch pans and pour mixture into them. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: grilled oysters
directions: Scrub oysters well.
Arrange oysters on grill grid.
Do not open shells!
Grill on uncovered grill, medium-hot Kingsford charcoal briquets, 12 to 15 minutes or until shells steam open. Discard ones that don't open.
While oysters are on grill, in a saucepan combine margarine, lemon juice and parsley.
Heat butter mixture on edge of grill until butter melts, stirring frequently. Carefully remove oysters from grill.
Spoon lemon butter mixture over top and serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vanilla shakes
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Pour into chilled glass and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil until fluffy.
Add flour, vanilla, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in zucchini and raisins.
Fill half a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 or 3 pans.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine enchilada sauce, tomatoes and tomato sauce with black beans.
Spread 1/3 of mixture in the bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with 3 uncooked lasagne noodles. Spread on the noodles one cup of cottage cheese and one cup of Cheddar cheese.
Cover with half of the remaining enchilada mixture.
Add another layer of noodles, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add another layer of noodles, rest of tomato sauce and last cup of cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until noodles are tender.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Split muffins and toast them; set aside.
Pour beaten egg in a 6 ounce custard cup.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at Medium for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until egg is set.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Mash egg with a fork until crumbly.
Combine egg and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Spread mixture over toasted muffins; microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until heated. Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley, if desired.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a 2-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or to 260° on a candy thermometer.

title: cristy's potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes to nearly fill a 9x13 pan. Melt 1 stick of real butter in pan.
Add potatoes.
Add salt and seasoned pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: aloha pie
directions: Line pie shells with thin sliced bananas; sprinkle with nuts. Cook pineapple, sugar and flour in double boiler until thickened. Cool.
Pour over bananas and nuts; sprinkle with coconut and top with Cool Whip.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Butter Bundt pan and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Throw in 24 Rhodes frozen dinner rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and butterscotch pudding (not instant).
Pour melted butter and sprinkle on the brown sugar.
Cover with towel and set overnight. Brush top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with foil and cook ten more minutes.

title: cocktail sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into small-sized balls. Place in baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, or until light brown.
May be frozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons margarine until soft.
Stir in flour; add water.
Cook over low heat until it boils.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli.
Add eggs and crumbs.
Mix gently. Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside. Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg and vanilla, mix well then add dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts.
Shape and roll dough into a roll about 2 1/2 or 3 inches in diameter.
Wrap cookie roll in wax paper or plastic wrap.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Slice into round slices about 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on cookie sheets in 400° oven for 7 to 10 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.
These are crispy crunchy cookies.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut fresh fruit into small pieces and put into large bowl; add coconut, container of yogurt and can of fruited cocktail.
Mix and chill in refrigerator for about 1 hour before serving.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix sugar and milk well.
Cook at medium heat until real thick.
Take off heat.
Stir peanut butter into mixture.
Pour in plates.
Put in the refrigerator.
Let it get cold and then cut into blocks.
Enjoy.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Cook bacon; remove from pan and drain.
Add onions and mushrooms to pan.
Cook until tender.
Add cream cheese to warm vegetables and soften.
Stir everything together except bread crumbs.
Pour everything into a buttered baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat pudding, milk and ice cream together until smooth.
Pour in pie crust (regular graham cracker or chocolate cookie).
Top with whipped topping.
Decorate with shaved chocolate or chocolate sprinkles.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and spread into pan. Spread the corn flakes over the potatoes. Drizzle the margarine over the corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange tea bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.

Combine the orange rind and sugar. Add to the flour mixture. In a separate bowl, combine and beat the egg, orange juice, milk and shortening. Pour the liquid mixture into the flour mixture. Fold in the walnuts, stirring until blended.
Divide the batter between two greased loaf pans and bake at 350° until done, about 50 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: indian spinach balls(serves 3 to 4 persons)
directions: Serve with rice and pita bread.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cut dates in small pieces.
Fix them first and set aside while mixing other ingredients.
Mix together thoroughly flour, salt, baking powder, soda, egg, vanilla and nuts.
Then add date mixture.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: beer barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; cook, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in onion and lemon.
Use sauce to baste chicken or ribs when grilling.

title: skillet pasta
directions: In electric skillet, brown beef and drain.
Add soup mix, oregano, water and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and add macaroni. Lower temperature to simmer and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Before serving, stir in Parmesan and top with Mozzarella.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Mix in pan and freeze overnight.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil until clear and cool.
Mix and, when you are ready to serve, add the club soda.
Delicious!

title: mamaw's chili
directions: Cook meat and onion with chili powder on stove top in skillet until brown and cooked through. Drain off ground meat. Combine meat and onions with diced tomatoes, chili beans and kidney beans in large pot. Add chili mix and stir. Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes or until warmed through.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and pudding mix together.
Stir in cold milk gradually.
Mix with electric mixer until thickened.
Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding mix and bananas in a large bowl.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with crushed vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and let sit in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together; cook in microwave for 3 minutes. Stir.
Cook on High 3 more minutes.
Stir.
Cook on High 3 more minutes.
Stir.
Cook on High 3 more minutes.
Stir.
(Total of 12 minutes.)
Watch carefully during cooking; may boil over. Mix in the peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour in buttered dish (approximately 10 x 12-inch).
Place in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of cake mix for topping.
Combine rest of cake mix and 1 stick of margarine.
Add one egg.
Press into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix pumpkin pie mix, milnot and 1 egg. Pour over cake mixture.
Combine reserved cake mix, pecans 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup margarine, melted.
Crumble and sprinkle over top.
Bake 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Chill 3 hours. Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into loaf pan.
Bake in a 400 degree oven for about an hour.

title: connie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars. Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheets. Press down with fork in checkerboard design.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes until golden brown. May be doubled. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onion, pepper, and celery.
Add beans and tomato juice and macaroni.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: carrot and potato bake
directions: Butter baking dish.
Layer half of potatoes, carrots, onions and cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle butter, crumbs and remaining cheese over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: southern fried okra
directions: Separate onion slices into rings.
Place rings in large bowl of ice water and let soak for 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, buttermilk, egg, vegetable oil, paprika and ground red pepper to form batter.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together until smooth.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted into cake will come out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then invert on wire rack to cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, salt and pumpkin spice together.
Add to creamed butter and sugar; mix.
Stir in oats. Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, 1/4 cup butter, vanilla and milk.
Place in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and remaining butter.
Top sweet potato casserole with crumb mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: orange coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar and grated orange rind. Remove biscuits from cans and drop each biscuit in melted butter and then in sugar mixture.
Arrange in an overlapping circle in a greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cream together cheese, orange juice, confectioners sugar and vanilla. While coffee ring is still warm, spread frosting over top and sprinkle with coconut.
Serve while warm.

title: chili
directions: Brown the hamburger in a large pan.
After meat has cooked, add the onion.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars and add beaten eggs.
Measure dry ingredients and mix well into 1st mixture.
Add fruit cocktail, raisins and nuts.
Pour into oblong casserole or cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add pretzel crumbs.
Pat in a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and beat.
Add Karo, milk, butter and pecans; mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake for 10 minutes in a preheated 400° oven; reduce heat to 375° and cook for another 40 minutes or until set, but not hard.

title: busy day chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Cover bottom evenly with uncooked rice.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour water into the pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
If browner chicken is desired, brown before placing it on the rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding and pineapple.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Cover bowl, chill and then it is ready to serve.

title: angelberry cake
directions: Using a mixer, combine cream cheese and topping until smooth and fluffy.
Frost bottom layer with mixture.
Spoon on 1/2 pie filling.
Place on top layer and completely frost sides and top with cream cheese mixture.
Place remainder of pie filling on top.

title: rockford's chili patty
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard, pickle, cheese and chili.
Freeze this mixture into patties.
When patties are frozen, make a pie crust and cover these patties with the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Broil in broiler until brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 pies.

title: chicken scallopini with mushrooms
directions: Place breast pieces between 2 sheets of waxed paper and pound with a mallet or other flat instrument to a thickness of about 1/8-inch.
Heat 2 tablespoons each of butter and oil in skillet. Add mushrooms and saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms and reserve.
Heat remaining butter and oil over medium-high heat.
Add breasts and saute, turning once, until browned, 4 to 5 minutes total cooking time.
Add shallots or green onions to pan and cook, scraping bottom until tender about 4 minutes.
Add white wine and broth, boil, reduce to simmer and cook until liquids are reduced by half.
Stir in cream and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and chicken and simmer to reheat.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put melted butter and salt over pecans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and place on platter.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Use with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: strawberry spritzer
directions: Place strawberries in container of electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Combine strawberry puree, white grape juice and carbonated water.
Yields 12 1/2 cups (122 calories per 1 1/4-cup serving).
Contains 0.4 g protein, 0.1 g fat, 31.4 g carbohydrate, 0 mg cholesterol, 24 mg sodium and 36 mg calcium.

title: almond roca(i make for althea at christmas)
directions: Line a 12 x 17-inch pan with finely chopped nuts.
Grate Hershey bar and sprinkle 1/2 over nuts.
Boil sugar, butter, Karo syrup and vanilla to hard crack stage at 350°, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over nuts and chocolate.
Sprinkle rest of Hershey bar and more nuts.
Press down.
Let cool.

title: aunt loretta's strawberry delight
directions: Crust:
Crush pretzels in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter or margarine mixed with 3 tablespoons sugar over pretzels. Coat thoroughly and press into pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: ricotta cake
directions: In a large bowl add to the flour the egg yolks, Ricotta, lemon rind, lemon juice and raisins.
Mix delicately.
Then add the baking powder and the whipped egg whites.
Stir the ingredients together and pour on a nonstick oven pan.
Cook on medium heat for about 1 hour.

title: pizza noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles to desired doneness; drain.
Heat oven to 350°. In large skillet, cook ground beef, onion and pepper for 7 to 9 minutes or until meat is brown and vegetables are crisp-tender; drain.
Add noodles, Italian seasoning, pepperoni, olives, tomato sauce and tomato paste; mix well.
Fold in 1 cup cheese.

title: diabetic date dainties
directions: Beat eggs, sweetener and baking powder. Add dates, flour and nuts. Stir in bread crumbs. Chill, then measure by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, milk, salt and sugar.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour, stirring several times.
Add lemon peel, nutmeg and raisins.
Continue baking for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Two-third cup brown sugar may be used in place of granulated sugar.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Place stuffing in bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Layer chicken on top of stuffing.
Cover with soup mixed with water. Cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May use turkey instead of chicken.

title: party applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and applesauce.
Add sifted dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Add boiling water with soda dissolved in it.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in bacon bits or pecans.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together and put into 2-8 in.
round cake pans.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 35 minutes.
Let cool COMPLETELY, then top with the following icing.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain water chestnuts, green beans and mushrooms.
Saute onions in butter and add all ingredients, except almonds.
