Mix well and pour into well-greased casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix together.
Add most of chopped beef to first 4 ingredients saving enough to sprinkle on top.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and oil to a boil and pour over corn, green beans, English peas, pimento and onion; toss lightly. Marinate in refrigerator, then serve cold or reheat and serve warm.

title: easy blackberry or fresh fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo in
baking
dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Put in dish on the oleo;
don't stir.
Put fruit on top of the mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese log
directions: Combine grated cheese, cream cheese, nuts and garlic powder. Mix thoroughly and form into two logs, 10 to 12 inches.
Roll in chili powder and chill.
Slice to use on crackers.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together
well
and
serve	with all kinds of fresh fruit. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: w.w.i.  wonder cake
directions: Mix together hot water, lard, sugar, raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Boil for 5 minutes; let cool.
Add flour and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with cream cheese or plain.
Serves 8.

title: hot artichoke dip(another dish that people will hover over.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor. Mix it up, then heat it in the microwave on High for 5 minutes. Serve with bread or something crunchy.

title: chicken luncheon casserole
directions: Mix together and spread in greased 9x12-inch (or 13-inch) pan. Cover and put in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300 degrees for 2 hours or 350 degrees for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Cut in serving pieces.
This can be baked, cooled and frozen and then reheated if there are leftovers.
Serves 12.

title: virginia chicken pudding
directions: Place the chicken, vegetables and seasonings in a heavy kettle, barely cover with water, and bring to a boil.
Skim off fat carefully, reduce heat, and simmer the chicken until it
is just tender.
Cool in the broth.
Strip chicken from the bones and place in a buttered baking dish.
Return bones and skin to the broth and reduce by half over moderate heat.
Strain broth and keep warm, discarding vegetables.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in pan and bake at 350 degrees until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: dream pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed, then fold in Cool Whip topping. Pour into pie shell and chill.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and cover with the following topping.

title: peach pizza
directions: In a bowl mix flour, pecans and butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: reduced fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Shedd spread, shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add vanilla and egg substitute; mix well.
Measure flours, baking soda and salt into small bowl.
Add gradually to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add chocolate chips and chopped walnuts to batter; fold into mixture.
Cook at 375° for 10 or 11 minutes until lightly browned.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: waikiki meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly first 7 ingredients.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoon into balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown and cook meat balls.
Remove meat balls; keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Boil Ronzoni in 4 cups water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender; drain and cool.
Drain juice of pineapple and oranges into saucepan.
Add sugar, eggs and flour.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly until thick like pudding.
Mix pineapple, oranges and cooled pasta gently; fold in pudding mixture.
Chill overnight or a whole day.
When ready to serve, add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Toss gently and enjoy.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Add the shortening and blend well.
The water should be hot, but not boiling.
Add water a little at a time, blending well.
The dough should be soft, but not sticky.
You may need a little more or less water.
Blend well and knead for 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead until very smooth.
Divide into little balls.
Cover and let rest for 30 to 40 minutes.
Roll out each ball as thin as possible, into 4 to 5-inch diameter circle.
Heat 1/2 cup shortening or oil in skillet and drop each piece of dough into the fat.
Press down in the center with a spoon.
Release.
When they are puffed up, turn and brown on the other side.
Drain them on paper towels and serve hot.
May be made in advance and reheated.
Makes about 24 pieces.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Roll into balls and deep fry. Cool; drain well. Serve as appetizer or put in sauce for main dish. They also freeze very well.

title: yogurt pie(low calorie)
directions: Mix
yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Pour into prepared graham cracker
crust.
Decorate with chocolate.	Refrigerate or freeze.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Place crust on baking sheet.
Pour in filling. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in from the edge is clean.

title: chocolate coconut crunches
directions: Combine and mix well cake mix, eggs and margarine.
Add and mix well coconut, walnuts, corn flakes and oats.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: butter jets
directions: Rub soft butter into sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and roll in desired shapes.
To melt chocolate, cut into small pieces and melt slowly in top of a double boiler.
Coat candies with melted chocolate and allow to harden.

title: pumpkin creme brulee(serves 6)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk and blend well.
Fill 6 (5 or 6 ounce) heat-proof custard cups with cream brulee mixture.

Place filled custard cups in a shallow baking pan and add hot water to fill pan 1-inch deep. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, until knife inserted in center of custard comes out clean.
Refrigerate cooled custard for 2 to 3 hours until set and well chilled.

title: king randi chicken
directions: Grease a deep 3-quart casserole dish.
Dip uncooked tortillas in chicken broth and alternate layers of tortillas, boned chicken pieces, onion, green pepper, cheese and chili powder.
Top with mushroom and chicken soups mixed with tomatoes and green chilies. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: angel delight
directions: Melt chocolate and water in double boiler.
Remove from heat. Beat in egg yolks, vanilla and sugar.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Cut cake into 3 layers.
Spread chocolate mixture in between, on sides and on top of all layers.
Refrigerate until set, approximately 1 hour.
When set, cover with whipped cream on top and on sides.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add rest of ingredients; bring to boil on low heat.
Boil soft ball.
Pour over corn and thoroughly mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 200° for about 20 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times while baking.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Cream sour cream and cream cheese until well blended; adding a couple tsps. of milk if necessary. Add minced onion, garlic powder and beef. Place in oven-proof dish. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: snickers brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix with 1/2 can of milk and melted margarine.
Press 2/3 of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.
While in oven, melt chopped caramels with other half of can of milk.
Pour this over the cooked cake mixture and sprinkle peanuts and chocolate chips over caramels. Sprinkle remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheesy meat pie
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add beef and onions.
Brown well and drain.
Place meat mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle grated cheese over meat.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients, then pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: ice cream royal
directions: Mix together pecans, flour, sugar and butter.
Spread on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Cool and crumble.
Spread half the crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream and place slices on top of crumbs.
Pour ice cream sauce on top of ice cream and top with rest of the crumbs.
Freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.
(Use any flavor of ice cream and sauce.)

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan over low heat. Cream remaining 1/2 cup butter and sugar in mixer bowl until fluffy.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add soda and sifted flour alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture and beating well after each addition. Stir in melted candy, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yields 12 to 24 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
When done, pull off bone and chop.
Spread rice over bottom of dish.
Moisten with broth from chicken.
Spread chopped chicken over rice.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Toss dressing with melted butter in 1 cup broth.
Spread over top of soup mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble into small pieces.
Mix rest of ingredients in large bowl, then mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 1/4 cup sugar and stir into mixture.

title: mam-ma's chicken in champagne
directions: Brush chicken with 1/4 cup butter and season lightly. Bake in a shallow dish at 375° for 25-30 minutes. For sauce, saute vegetables in 1/4 cup butter until soft but not brown. Add wine, salt, pepper and sugar and heat to boiling. Let boil for 10 minutes. Blend small amount of flour with water and stir quickly into sauce to thicken. Stir sauce constantly. Add pan drippings from chicken to sauce. Lower heat and stir in cream. Do not let boil. Pour sauce over chicken breasts. Enjoy!

title: rice dressing
directions: Oil bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup rice on bottom of dish.
Chop one small onion, 2 stalks celery and a small can pimento on top of rice.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1 can cream of celery soup and 2 small cans of chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 2 1/2 cups water on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken; place in bottom of large casserole dish. Add both cans of soup plus 2 cans
water
(or
enough to cover chicken).
Add rice and stir together.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green bean salad
directions: Heat beans, but not to a boiling point.
Drain well.
Add chopped vegetables and French dressing.
Toss lightly and serve immediately.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: basic recipe for rolls, doughnuts or sweet rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, but flour; blend well.
Add 5 cups flour; beat until smooth with a wooden spoon.
(Very important to beat until little bubbles can be seen in dough.)
Let rise once; beat down with wooden spoon.
Pour out on well floured board.
Do not knead; just pat out or roll to thickness desired.
Let rest. Cut out your doughnuts, dinner rolls or cinnamon rolls.

title: souped up minute rice
directions: Empty can of soup into saucepan.
(Do not add water.) Bring soup to a boil; stir in rice (measure with soup can).
Cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: french meat pie
directions: In a skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onions until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Brown beef and pork together. Drain.
Combine onion, meat, potato and seasonings.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Make slits on top crust.
Brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Bon appetit.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: work person's roast
directions: Season roast to your taste.
I use garlic and onion to stuff it.
Place in a large Dutch oven.
Add chopped onion and a can of cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over the top and cover.
Place in 200° to 250° oven before work.
At supper time, it is done to perfection with wonderful gravy.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water; cook slowly until it reaches 236°.
Add nuts and salt; cook until temperature reaches 295°. Add butter and soda; remove from heat.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Prepare dates, candy and nuts by cutting up finely and roll in a portion of the flour.
Cream butter with the sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well.
Add buttermilk.
Stir together the remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in dates, nuts and orange slices.
Add coconut.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Leave cake in pan and frost with the Orange Slice Frosting.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients except butter. Mix well; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour butter over top and bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
This freezes well.

title: barbecued rabbit
directions: Combine all
sauce
ingredients
and simmer 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Baste
quartered rabbits generously with sauce and grill over charcoal.
Turn every 5 minutes and baste heavily each time.
Meat
should be ready to fall off the bone in 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve
with
corn
on the cob, cole slaw and fresh rolls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake meatballs on broiler pan (not touching) at 375° for 20 minutes.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in saucepan, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until thoroughly coated.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen appetizers.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli and cauliflower together in boiling water until tender; drain.
Stir in condensed soup, cheese spread and 1/2 the onions into the drained vegetables.
Turn vegetable mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions atop and bake for 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Parboil chicken and broccoli (in separate pans) for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from bones; cut into chunks.
Layer chicken and broccoli in buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli, spreading to edges of pan.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate satin glaze
directions: Combine sugar and water in small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils and sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add mini chips; stir until melted. Continue until glaze is desired consistency.

title: lite creamy peanut butter pie
directions: In a bowl whisk milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes. Stir in peanut butter.
Transfer to crust.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Just before serving, spread with whipped topping and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Chill
milk
in
freezer
until almost frozen solid and whip. Add lemon juice and rind, beating all the time.
Continue beating, adding
the sugar slowly.	Crush the crackers and cover the bottom
of	a
cake
pan.
Save
about
1 cup of the crackers for later.
Spoon the mixture over your crust and top with remaining crackers.

title: homemade pot pies
directions: Cook bottom layer until almost done.
(If not cooked, crust will be doughy.)
Add your choice of filling.
Mix Bisquick as directed for biscuits.
Cover the top completely.
Bake until top crust is golden brown.

title: texas millionaires
directions: In a double boiler, melt caramels, margarine and water.
When melted, add nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper or a buttered cookie sheet. Allow to cool and harden.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Melt teaspoon butter in 6-inch skillet.
Pour 1/2 cup mixture in skillet.
Cook until set. Brown on edges.
Turn and brown on other side.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli. Mix well with cheese and onion.
Store overnight.

title: jerome cookies
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt margarine and mix with sugar.
Add beaten egg to canned milk.
Mix with margarine and sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs to mixture and pour over graham crackers in pan.
Put layers of whole crackers on top.

title: kathy's brownies
directions: Blend margarine, sugar, eggs.
Add cocoa, baking powder and salt, then vanilla and finally flour and nuts.
Pour into greased, but not floured pan and bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chunky vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine. Saute butter and celery 5 minutes or until almost tender. Add broth, potatoes and carrots. Cover; simmer 15 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes with liquid and remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.

title: raspberry-chocolate sauce
directions: Heat chocolate chips and water on low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Add milk and liquor.
Serve warm or cool on ice cream, cake, fruit or cheesecake.

title: beans for strict fast
directions: In a saucepan, heat through the beans and the can of tomatoes, add salt to taste.
In a skillet, heat the oil; add flour and brown, making a smooth paste.
Add slowly to bean mixture to thicken.
Cook through until heated.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Prepare bow tie pasta; rinse and drain.
Let cook and set aside.
Rinse and drain asparagus, then cut into 1/2-inch sections.
Set aside.
Rinse and drain hearts of palm.
Cut into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Set aside.
Rinse and drain artichoke hearts and section like a pie into 6 or 8 sections.
Set aside.
Cube cheese and set aside.
Combine vegetables, cheese and pasta in bowl.
Mix oil and vinegar and spices to taste.
Sprinkle over salad.
Toss lightly.
Enjoy!

title: honey soy wings
directions: In medium bowl, mix honey, soy sauce and ginger.
Coat wings with mixture; allow to marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: punch
directions: This is very good for colds, sore throats or flu.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in large container with lid or may use blender.
Blend well; refrigerate unused portion.

title: cinnamon peanut cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on ungreased sheets.
You can crisscross with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: french market soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Cook slowly until done.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 10 minutes.
Keep warm at 200°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour in freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Arrange nuts in a shallow pan; add 2 teaspoons butter.
Cook until brown at 325°.
Remove from pan; cool.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in the pan.
Beat egg whites until moist peaks form.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon; fold into egg whites.
Stir nuts into mixture.
Spread them out over the melted butter, forming 1 layer. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salmon dyonnaise
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise, mustard and dill.
Mix in buttermilk.
Cover.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve over salmon or any fish or vegetable.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tutti-frutti ice sparkle
directions: Take out a large pitcher or bowl, measuring cups, spoon, ice cube trays and glasses.
Mix each flavor Kool-Aid with 2/3 cup sugar and 4 cups water.
Pour into separate ice trays.
Freeze. To serve, put 1 cube of each flavor in a tall glass and fill with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Blend in Cool Whip. Pour int graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling (1 can cherry pie filling tops both pies).
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: oven chipped potatoes
directions: Use large shallow greased metal baking pan.
Scrub the potatoes and have oven preheating to 425°.
Melt the butter or margarine and combine with the onion, salt and pepper.
Let stand on warm burner while slicing potatoes.
Do not peel the potatoes (the skin adds texture).
Slice up to 1/4-inch thick or as thin as you like.
Arrange the slices in a shallow pan which has been generously greased with shortening.
Brush the melted butter mixture on potato slices and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour, reducing oven temperature if necessary, part way through baking time. Serve with catsup or sour cream.
Bake at 425° (at least for the first half hour, then reduce temperature if necessary).

title: peanut butter cookies(sugar-free)
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together mashed banana, peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Beat well.
Stir in chopped peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly oiled cookie sheets.
Press each cookie with back of a fork and again in opposite direction.
(Wet fork with cold water occasionally to avoid sticking.)
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks. Makes 2 to 3 dozen light, soft cookies.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Grease casserole well.
Spread rice in casserole and add water.
Place chicken breasts on rice.
Cover with onion soup, mushroom soup, parsley and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: candy bars
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar and oats together.
Bake in greased jelly roll size baking sheet with 1-inch side for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Spread with peanut butter while still warm.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and spread over peanut butter.
Cool in fridge.
Cut into bar size pieces.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions.
In a large skillet, heat oil; add shrimp and garlic.
Stir and cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add hot linguine, Parmesan cheese, dill, salt and pepper. Toss well to coat linguine.
Add a little butter or milk if needed to make creamy.

title: minced meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, deviled ham, salt and pepper. Add beef and mix well. Shape into bite size meatballs. Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes. Cool and remove from pan. (Can be frozen at this point.) When ready to serve, combine pie filling, apple juice and vinegar. Heat through. Add meatballs and simmer. Keep warm. Add more juice if mixture becomes too thick.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions across top and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Pat in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all above together.

title: kutya
directions: Soak wheat in 2 cups of water for 4 hours.
Cook until desired tenderness.
Meanwhile, cook honey with water and add poppy seed; add nuts.
Serve cold with the wheat.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In a 1-quart pan, mix chicken broth and cornstarch until smooth.
Cook over high heat, stirring frequently until it comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Stirring constantly, pour beaten egg in thin stream into simmering broth.
Stir in green onions and serve.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry meats separately.
Drain on paper towels.
Put meats back in skillet.
Add spices and cheese until cheese is melted.
Spoon onto party rye.
Place on cookie sheets and place in freezer until frozen.
Once frozen, you may place them in storage bags and put back into freezer until ready to serve.

title: three vegetable dish
directions: Peel and cut in medium size pieces.
Cook in boiling water, with 1 tablespoon salt added, until soft.
Mash with hand masher to coarse consistency.
Add butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into greased glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and top with grated cheese (about 2 cups).
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: quick and easy mock hollandaise sauce
directions: In the top of a double boiler over medium heat, blend hot water with mayonnaise, stirring, until thoroughly heated.
Add lemon juice and stir to mix well.
This sauce may be served with broccoli, asparagus, cauliflower or other vegetables.
Makes 1/2 cup.
Serves 8 (1 tablespoon per serving).

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in a medium bowl with a wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In top of a double boiler, mix sugar, salt and flour. Stir in milk, egg yolks. Cook until slightly thickened. Stir in peanut butter and cook until thick. Add vanilla. Cool, pour into baked pie crust. Add meringue.

title: fruit salad
directions: First scoop out inside of a watermelon so it is empty.
Then mix all ingredients in it.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Combine vegetables, parsley flakes, salt, pepper, water and bouillon cube.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Mix milk and flour; add to hot vegetables.
Heat and stir until boiling and thickened.
Cube cheese; add to soup.
Stir until melted.

title: salsa fresca
directions: Chop up tomatoes, onion, peppers and cilantro.
Add lime juice.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: pepper steak beef dish
directions: Cut meat into inch squares.
Brown meat in oil, stirring often, for about 20 minutes.
Add onion and crushed garlic during last minutes of browning.
Add other seasonings, tomato puree and 1/2 cup of the water.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour, stirring occasionally and adding remaining water gradually as liquid evaporates.
Add chopped sweet peppers and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot over noodles, rice or whipped potatoes.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Place all vegetables in food chopper.
Mix other ingredients. Cook over medium heat for 1 hour or until done.
Seal in jars.

title: tuna and potato chip casserole
directions: Add drained tuna, peas, soup and milk.
Mix well.
Add chips. Mix again.
Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May microwave if you like for 15 minutes on High.
Stir and microwave another 15 minutes.

title: gallon vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pinch of salt, sugar, vanilla and carton of cream.
Put dasher in the ice cream can.
Pour ingredients into can.
Fill the container 2 inches from the top.
Put container in hot water in a deep well to get warm.
When the mixture is warm, add rennet tablets. Turn dashers 1 time.
Let set in warm water 10 minutes, then pour in your ice cream tub. Put ice and ice cream salt in the tub.
Turn until frozen.
Delicious!

title: pickled walnuts
directions: To each quart of water allow 2 ounces of whole black pepper. Procure the walnuts while young; be careful they are not woody, and prick them well with a fork.
Prepare a strong brine of salt and water (4 pounds salt to each 1 gallon of water).
Add the walnuts and set 9 days.
Change the brine every third day, drain them off and put them on a dish, place it in the sun until they become perfectly black, which will be in 2 or 3 days.
Have dry jars ready, put in the walnuts, do not quite fill the jar.

title: favorite cornbread(from mrs. camp, henderson, texas)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(I usually mix the buttermilk and soda together before pouring into other ingredients.)
Bake at 450° until brown on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: In medium size bowl, mix together eggs, tomato sauce, spices, Worcestershire sauce and oats.
Stir in onion and green pepper. Add turkey and turkey sausage to mixture and mix in well.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan (spray pan with nonstick spray). Bake, uncovered, in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: carrot or zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs; add oil and beat together. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well, then add grated carrots or zucchini.
Lastly, add the nuts and/or raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan for 40 minutes or until done.
Top with a Cream Cheese Frosting.
It's delicious!

title: chocolate bit bars
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts last.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Cool in pan.
Cut in bars.

title: just for kids: choc'laty sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, salt and water.
Place over medium heat.
Boil 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix spinach, sour cream, onion soup mix and chopped artichoke hearts together.
Place in casserole; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Blend shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder (which have been sifted together) and blend.
Add oatmeal, nuts and pineapple and blend.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla in a sauce pan. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in peanut butter. Remove from heat. Add oats and mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper. Let cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt, garlic and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and spaghetti sauce.
Mix and simmer 30 minutes.
Boil noodles according to directions and drain. Alternate layers, sauce, noodles, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients with hands (butter hands for easier mixing).
Place in 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and refrigerate.
Decorate top with pecan halves.

title: election cake
directions: Stir milk, sugar and yeast to a batter and let stand overnight; in the morning, add sugar, butter, eggs, nutmeg, cinnamon, raisins and brandy.
Brown sugar is much better than white for this kind of cake and it is improved by dissolving a half-teaspoon of soda in a tablespoon of milk in the morning.
It should stand in the greased pans and rise some time until quite light before baking.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour and salt.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time and stir in Carnation milk. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 250° and bake for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and flour with a wire whisk.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake in a buttered dish for 1 hour in 325°
oven. Serves 6.

title: manicotti with cheese stuffing
directions: Cook the manicotti according to directions for parboiling. Mix together remaining 5 ingredients.
Stuff tubes with cheese mixture.

title: rio grande valley grapefruit pie
directions: Cut marshmallows in quarters.
Melt them in 1/4 cup grapefruit juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Add remaining 1/4 cup juice to sections.
Whip cream.
Fold cooled marshmallows, grapefruit and cream together.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Allow to set about 3 hours.
Sprinkle coconut over pie just before serving.

title: orange-cinnamon snaps
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°F.
Beat 1 cup sugar, shortening, egg, vanilla, and orange rind together.
Add orange juice.
Stir in flour, soda, and salt.
Shape dough into walnut-size balls. Combine 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Dip balls in the sugar-cinnamon mixture and place each on a baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in additional sugar.
Bake 10-15 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: frozen juice punch
directions: Mix ingredients just before serving.
Pour over ice or frozen ice ring.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: grilled orange roughy
directions: Combine lemon juice, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper.
Whisk in olive oil.
Marinate fillets for 30 to 60 minutes.
Grill 5 to 6 minutes per side.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Mix together and put into an 8 x 8-inch pan (well-greased). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: taco soup 1
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with sour cream, grated cheese and tortillas.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar to soft ball stage, using low heat and boil for about 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Beat well and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into large buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: no-name cake!!!
directions: Blend cake mix and melted butter and press down in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle peanut butter chips and butterscotch chips on top.
Sprinkle pecans on top of chips. Drizzle Eagle Brand milk on top of everything.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: gladys' baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy and cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg and beat one minute. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla. Blend in marshmallows and chocolate bits. Pour in greased pan. Mix brown sugar, butter and nuts together. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg drop noodle soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except egg; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until noodles are tender.
With fork, gently stir in beaten egg until egg is cooked.
Makes about 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 1 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll dough into balls and roll in sugar mixture.
Drop in greased round cake pan.
In pan, heat margarine, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Heat until mixed good, then pour over balls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn upside down.

title: split pea and potato soup
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onions; cook until soft. Stir in beef broth and water and bring to a boil.
Add peas and potatoes.
Cover and cook slowly until tender.
Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind all vegetables and mix with sugar and vinegar.
Boil 1 hour; drain well.
After drained add salad dressing and mustard. Mix well.
Put in small jars and share with friends and neighbors. Recipe may be halved or quartered.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: swedish spice cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beat until light and fluffy. Beat in molasses and egg. Combine flour, salt, spices, orange peel, and baking soda. Gradually add to cream mixture. Gather dough into a ball; wrap in plastic wrap. Chill 2 to 3 hours. Preheat oven to 375°. Use 1/4 dough at a time; keep remainder refrigerated until needed. Sprinkle pastry cloth and rolling pin with granulated sugar. Sprinkle top of dough with sugar also. Roll to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut with floured cookie cutters. Place 1-inch apart on unbuttered cookie sheets. If planning to use as ornaments make small hole near the top of the cookie using tip of wooden pick.
Use a silver dragee for eye. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely on wire racks. Decorate with icing, store in airtight containers at room temperature.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Stir in almonds; mix well.

title: texas pecan candy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine cherries and pineapple in large bowl.
Sprinkle with flour, toss to coat well.
Add coconut and pecans, toss and mix.
Add sweetened cream, mix well.
Spoon into tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan and wrap in foil and refrigerate approximately 2 weeks.

title: cooked meringue
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch. Cook over medium heat. stir constantly until clear and thick. Beat egg whites and salt until foamy. Continue heating while gradually pouring cooked meringue into egg whites. Beat 3 minutes or until stiff, peaks form. Do Not Overheat.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Put on greased cookie sheet at 350° until light brown around edges.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in margarine until clear.
Add soups, stock, chilies and seasonings.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put layer of chunked tortillas, 1/2 of sauce and 1/2 of chicken.
Repeat layers. Top with grated cheese and bake about 30 minutes in medium oven. Let set about 15 minutes before serving.

title: m'm good taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes.
Prick bottom of pie shell thoroughly with a fork.
Bake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.

title: frozen punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Dissolve Jell-O; add.
Cool and add juices.
Mix well.
Freeze in plastic bowl, quart to 1/2-gallon size.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup strawberries in a small saucepan; add water. Bring to boiling point; simmer for 3 minutes.
Strain juice from cooked berries; add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch; slowly add berry juice.
Stir until smooth.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Cook until thick and clear; remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Put remaining berries in pie shell; cover with glaze and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg, onion and garlic.
Add parsley, basil, salt, pepper, tomatoes and paste.
Stir; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Meanwhile, cook noodles in salt water and vegetable oil for 20 to 25 minutes.
Rinse and cool; separate.
Preheat oven to 350°. Repeat layers in this order:
noodles, cottage or Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese, ending with meat sauce.
Repeat 2 or 3 times.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Stir everything together except shrimp.
Then mix with shrimp. Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then broil for 5 minutes.
